Array.name: Array
Array.description: Generic array, contains several elements of any type, accessible by numerical index starting at 0. Negative indices can be used to count from the right, like in Python. Arrays are always passed by reference.

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolColorArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolVector3Array].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolVector2Array].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolStringArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolRealArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolIntArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolByteArray].

methods.name: append
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array (alias of [method push_back]).

methods.name: back
methods.description: Returns the last element of the array if the array is not empty (size>0).

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the array (resize to 0).

methods.name: count
methods.description: Return the amount of times an element is in the array.

methods.name: empty
methods.description: Return true if the array is empty (size==0).

methods.name: erase
methods.description: Remove the first occurrence of a value from the array.

methods.name: find
methods.description: Searches the array for a value and returns its index or -1 if not found. Optionally, the initial search index can be passed.

methods.name: find_last
methods.description: Searches the array in reverse order for a value and returns its index or -1 if not found.

methods.name: front
methods.description: Returns the first element of the array if the array is not empty (size>0).

methods.name: has
methods.description:
Return true if the array contains given value.
				[codeblock]
				[ "inside", 7 ].has("inside") == true
				[ "inside", 7 ].has("outside") == false
				[ "inside", 7 ].has(7) == true
				[ "inside", 7 ].has("7") == false
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: hash
methods.description: Return a hashed integer value representing the array contents.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last).

methods.name: pop_back
methods.description: Remove the last element of the array.

methods.name: pop_front
methods.description: Remove the first element of the array.

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array.

methods.name: push_front
methods.description: Add an element at the beginning of the array.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Resize the array to contain a different number of elements. If the array size is smaller, elements are cleared, if bigger, new elements are Null.

methods.name: rfind
methods.description: Searches the array in reverse order. Optionally, a start search index can be passed. If negative, the start index is considered relative to the end of the array.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the amount of elements in the array.

methods.name: sort
methods.description: Sort the array using natural order.

methods.name: sort_custom
methods.description: Sort the array using a custom method. The arguments are an object that holds the method and the name of such method. The custom method receives two arguments (a pair of elements from the array) and must return true if the first argument is less than the second, and return false otherwise.

methods.name: add_surface_from_arrays
methods.description:
Create a new surface ([method get_surface_count] that will become surf_idx for this.
				Surfaces are created to be rendered using a "primitive", which may be PRIMITIVE_POINTS, PRIMITIVE_LINES, PRIMITIVE_LINE_STRIP, PRIMITIVE_LINE_LOOP, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_STRIP, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_FAN. (As a note, when using indices, it is recommended to only use just points, lines or triangles).

methods.name: get_surface_count
methods.description: Return the amount of surfaces that the [ArrayMesh] holds.

methods.name: surface_get_array_index_len
methods.description: Return the length in indices of the index array in the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_array_len
methods.description: Return the length in vertices of the vertex array in the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_format
methods.description: Return the format mask of the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_material
methods.description: Return a [Material] in a given surface. Surface is rendered using this material.

methods.name: surface_get_primitive_type
methods.description: Return the primitive type of the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_remove
methods.description: Remove a surface at position surf_idx, shifting greater surfaces one surf_idx slot down.

methods.name: surface_set_name
methods.description: Set a [Material] for a given surface. Surface will be rendered using this material.

constants.name: NO_INDEX_ARRAY
constants.description: Default value used for index_array_len when no indices are present.

constants.name: ARRAY_WEIGHTS_SIZE
constants.description: Amount of weights/bone indices per vertex (always 4).

constants.name: ARRAY_TANGENT
constants.description: Tangent array, array of groups of 4 floats. first 3 floats determine the tangent, and the last the binormal direction as -1 or 1.

constants.name: ARRAY_TEX_UV
constants.description: UV array (array of [Vector3] UVs or float array of groups of 2 floats (u,v)).

constants.name: ARRAY_TEX_UV2
constants.description: Second UV array (array of [Vector3] UVs or float array of groups of 2 floats (u,v)).

constants.name: ARRAY_BONES
constants.description: Array of bone indices, as a float array. Each element in groups of 4 floats.

constants.name: ARRAY_WEIGHTS
constants.description: Array of bone weights, as a float array. Each element in groups of 4 floats.

constants.name: ARRAY_INDEX
constants.description: Array of integers, used as indices referencing vertices. No index can be beyond the vertex array size.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_COLOR
constants.description: Array format will include a color array.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_TEX_UV2
constants.description: Array format will include another set of UVs.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_BONES
constants.description: Array format will include bone indices.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_WEIGHTS
constants.description: Array format will include bone weights.

AudioServer.name: AudioServer
AudioServer.brief_description: Server interface for low level audio access.
AudioServer.description: AudioServer is a low level server interface for audio access. It is in charge of creating sample data (playable audio) as well as its playback via a voice interface.

AudioStream.name: AudioStream
AudioStream.description: Base class for audio streams. Audio streams are used for music playback, or other types of streamed sounds that don't fit or require more flexibility than a [Sample].

BackBufferCopy.name: BackBufferCopy
BackBufferCopy.brief_description: Copies a region of the screen (or the whole screen) to a buffer so it can be accessed with the texscreen() shader instruction.
BackBufferCopy.description: Node for back-buffering the currently displayed screen. The region defined in the BackBufferCopy node is bufferized with the content of the screen it covers, or the entire screen according to the copy mode set. Accessing this buffer is done with the texscreen() shader instruction.

methods.name: get_copy_mode
methods.description: Return the copy mode currently applied to the BackBufferCopy (refer to constants section).

methods.name: get_rect
methods.description: Return the area covered by the BackBufferCopy.

methods.name: set_copy_mode
methods.description: Set the copy mode of the BackBufferCopy (refer to constants section).

methods.name: set_rect
methods.description: Defines the area covered by the BackBufferCopy.

constants.name: COPY_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Disables the buffering mode. This means the BackBufferCopy node will directly use the portion of screen it covers.

constants.name: COPY_MODE_RECT
constants.description: Sets the copy mode to a region.

constants.name: COPY_MODE_VIEWPORT
constants.description: Sets the copy mode to the entire screen.

BaseButton.name: BaseButton
BaseButton.brief_description: Provides a base class for different kinds of buttons.
BaseButton.description: BaseButton is the abstract base class for buttons, so it shouldn't be used directly (It doesn't display anything). Other types of buttons inherit from it.

methods.name: _pressed
methods.description: Called when button is pressed.

methods.name: _toggled
methods.description: Called when button is toggled (only if toggle_mode is active).

methods.name: get_action_mode
methods.description: Return the current mode of action (see [method set_action_mode]) (one of the ACTION_MODE_* constants).

methods.name: get_draw_mode
methods.description: Return the visual state used to draw the button. This is useful mainly when implementing your own draw code by either overriding _draw() or connecting to "draw" signal. The visual state of the button is defined by the DRAW_* enum.

methods.name: get_enabled_focus_mode
methods.description: Returns focus access mode used when switching between enabled/disabled (see [method Control.set_focus_mode] and [method set_disabled]).

methods.name: is_disabled
methods.description: Return whether the button is in disabled state (see [method set_disabled]).

methods.name: is_hovered
methods.description: Return true if mouse entered the button before it exit.

methods.name: is_pressed
methods.description: If toggle_mode is active, return whether the button is toggled. If toggle_mode is not active, return whether the button is pressed down.

methods.name: is_toggle_mode
methods.description: Return the toggle_mode property (see [method set_toggle_mode]).

methods.name: set_action_mode
methods.description: Set the current mode of action, determining when the button is considered clicked (see the ACTION_MODE_* constants).

methods.name: set_disabled
methods.description: Set the button into disabled state. When a button is disabled, it can't be clicked or toggled.

methods.name: set_enabled_focus_mode
methods.description: Sets the focus access mode to use when switching between enabled/disabled (see [method Control.set_focus_mode] and [method set_disabled]).

methods.name: set_pressed
methods.description: Set the button to pressed state (only if toggle_mode is active).

methods.name: set_toggle_mode
methods.description: Set the button toggle_mode property. Toggle mode makes the button flip state between pressed and unpressed each time its area is clicked.

signals.name: button_down
signals.description: Emitted when the button starts being held down.

signals.name: button_up
signals.description: Emitted when the button stops being held down.

signals.name: pressed
signals.description: This signal is emitted every time the button is toggled or pressed (i.e. activated, so on [code]button_down[/code] if "Click on press" is active and on [code]button_up[/code] otherwise).

signals.name: toggled
signals.description: This signal is emitted when the button was just toggled between pressed and normal states (only if toggle_mode is active). The new state is contained in the [i]pressed[/i] argument.

constants.name: DRAW_NORMAL
constants.description: The normal state (i.e. not pressed, not hovered, not toggled and enabled) of buttons.

constants.name: DRAW_PRESSED
constants.description: The state of buttons are pressed.

constants.name: DRAW_HOVER
constants.description: The state of buttons are hovered.

constants.name: DRAW_DISABLED
constants.description: The state of buttons are disabled.

constants.name: ACTION_MODE_BUTTON_PRESS
constants.description: Require just a press to consider the button clicked.

constants.name: ACTION_MODE_BUTTON_RELEASE
constants.description: Require a press and a subsequent release before considering the button clicked.

Basis.name: Basis
Basis.description:
3x3 matrix used for 3D rotation and scale. Contains 3 vector fields x,y and z as its columns, which can be interpreted as the local basis vectors of a transformation. Can also be accessed as array of 3D vectors. These vectors are orthogonal to each other, but are not necessarily normalized. Almost always used as orthogonal basis for a [Transform].
		For such use, it is composed of a scaling and a rotation matrix, in that order (M = R.S).

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a rotation matrix from the given quaternion.

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a rotation matrix (in the XYZ convention: first Z, then Y, and X last) from the specified Euler angles, given in the vector format as (third, second, first).

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a rotation matrix which rotates around the given axis by the specified angle. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a matrix from 3 axis vectors.

methods.name: determinant
methods.description: Return the determinant of the matrix.

methods.name: get_euler
methods.description: Assuming that the matrix is a proper rotation matrix (orthonormal matrix with determinant +1), return Euler angles (in the XYZ convention: first Z, then Y, and X last). Returned vector contains the rotation angles in the format (third,second,first).

methods.name: get_orthogonal_index
methods.description: This function considers a discretization of rotations into 24 points on unit sphere, lying along the vectors (x,y,z) with each component being either -1,0 or 1, and returns the index of the point best representing the orientation of the object. It is mainly used by the grid map editor. For further details, refer to Godot source code.

methods.name: get_scale
methods.description: Assuming that the matrix is the combination of a rotation and scaling, return the absolute value of scaling factors along each axis.

methods.name: inverse
methods.description: Return the inverse of the matrix.

methods.name: orthonormalized
methods.description: Return the orthonormalized version of the matrix (useful to call from time to time to avoid rounding error for orthogonal matrices). This performs a Gram-Schmidt orthonormalization on the basis of the matrix.

methods.name: rotated
methods.description: Introduce an additional rotation around the given axis by phi (radians). Only relevant when the matrix is being used as a part of [Transform]. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: scaled
methods.description: Introduce an additional scaling specified by the given 3D scaling factor. Only relevant when the matrix is being used as a part of [Transform].

methods.name: set_rotation_axis_angle
methods.description: Changes only the rotation part of the [Basis] to a rotation around given axis by phi, while preserving the scaling part (as determined by get_scale).

methods.name: set_rotation_euler
methods.description: Changes only the rotation part of the [Basis] to a rotation corresponding to given Euler angles, while preserving the scaling part (as determined by get_scale).

methods.name: set_scale
methods.description: Changes only the scaling part of the Basis to the specified scaling, while preserving the rotation part (as determined by get_rotation).

methods.name: tdotx
methods.description: Transposed dot product with the x axis of the matrix.

methods.name: tdoty
methods.description: Transposed dot product with the y axis of the matrix.

methods.name: tdotz
methods.description: Transposed dot product with the z axis of the matrix.

methods.name: transposed
methods.description: Return the transposed version of the matrix.

methods.name: xform
methods.description: Return a vector transformed (multiplied) by the matrix.

methods.name: xform_inv
methods.description: Return a vector transformed (multiplied) by the transposed matrix. Note that this results in a multiplication by the inverse of the matrix only if it represents a rotation-reflection.

methods.name: add_char
methods.description: Add a character to the font, where [i]character[/i] is the unicode value, [i]texture[/i] is the texture index, [i]rect[/i] is the region in the texture (in pixels!), [i]align[/i] is the (optional) alignment for the character and [i]advance[/i] is the (optional) advance.

methods.name: add_kerning_pair
methods.description: Add a kerning pair to the [BitmapFont] as a difference. Kerning pairs are special cases where a typeface advance is determined by the next character.

methods.name: add_texture
methods.description: Add a texture to the [BitmapFont].

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all the font data.

methods.name: get_char_size
methods.description: Return the size of a character, optionally taking kerning into account if the next character is provided.

methods.name: get_kerning_pair
methods.description: Return a kerning pair as a difference.

methods.name: set_ascent
methods.description: Set the font ascent (number of pixels above the baseline).

methods.name: set_height
methods.description: Set the total font height (ascent plus descent) in pixels.

BoneAttachment.name: BoneAttachment
BoneAttachment.brief_description: A node that will attach to a bone.
BoneAttachment.description: This node must be the child of a [Skeleton] node. You can then select a bone for this node to attach to. The BoneAttachment node will copy the transform of the selected bone.

BoxContainer.name: BoxContainer
BoxContainer.description: Base class for Box containers. It arranges children controls vertically or horizontally, and rearranges them automatically when their minimum size changes.

methods.name: add_spacer
methods.description:
Add a control to the box as a spacer.
				If [i]begin[/i] is true the spacer control will be inserted in front of other children.

methods.name: get_alignment
methods.description: Return the alignment of children in the container.

methods.name: set_alignment
methods.description: Set the alignment of children in the container(Must be one of ALIGN_BEGIN, ALIGN_CENTER or ALIGN_END).

constants.name: ALIGN_BEGIN
constants.description: Align children with beginning of the container.

constants.name: ALIGN_CENTER
constants.description: Align children with center of the container.

constants.name: ALIGN_END
constants.description: Align children with end of the container.

BoxShape.name: BoxShape
BoxShape.description: Box shape resource, which can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or area.

methods.name: get_extents
methods.description: Return the half extents of the shape.

methods.name: set_extents
methods.description: Set the half extents for the shape.

Button.name: Button
Button.description: Button is the standard themed button. It can contain text and an icon, and will display them according to the current [Theme].

methods.name: get_button_icon
methods.description: Return the button icon.

methods.name: get_clip_text
methods.description: Return the state of the [i]clip_text[/i] property (see [method set_clip_text])

methods.name: get_text
methods.description: Return the button text.

methods.name: get_text_align
methods.description: Return the text alignment policy.

methods.name: is_flat
methods.description: Return the state of the [i]flat[/i] property (see [method set_flat]).

methods.name: set_button_icon
methods.description: Set the icon that will be displayed next to the text inside the button area.

methods.name: set_clip_text
methods.description: Set the [i]clip_text[/i] property of a Button. When this property is enabled, text that is too large to fit the button is clipped, when disabled (default) the Button will always be wide enough to hold the text.

methods.name: set_flat
methods.description: Set the [i]flat[/i] property of a Button. Flat buttons don't display decoration unless hovered or pressed.

methods.name: set_text
methods.description: Set the button text, which will be displayed inside the button area.

methods.name: set_text_align
methods.description: Set the text alignment policy, using one of the ALIGN_* constants.

constants.name: ALIGN_LEFT
constants.description: Align the text to the left.

constants.name: ALIGN_RIGHT
constants.description: Align the text to the right.

ButtonGroup.name: ButtonGroup
ButtonGroup.description: Group of [Button]. All direct and indirect children buttons become radios. Only one allows being pressed.

methods.name: get_pressed_button
methods.description: Return the pressed button.

Camera.name: Camera
Camera.brief_description: Camera node, displays from a point of view.
Camera.description: Camera is a special node that displays what is visible from its current location. Cameras register themselves in the nearest [Viewport] node (when ascending the tree). Only one camera can be active per viewport. If no viewport is available ascending the tree, the Camera will register in the global viewport. In other words, a Camera just provides [i]3D[/i] display capabilities to a [Viewport], and, without one, a scene registered in that [Viewport] (or higher viewports) can't be displayed.

methods.name: get_camera_transform
methods.description: Get the camera transform. Subclassed cameras (such as CharacterCamera) may provide different transforms than the [Node] transform.

methods.name: is_current
methods.description: Return whether the Camera is the current one in the [Viewport], or plans to become current (if outside the scene tree).

methods.name: make_current
methods.description: Make this camera the current Camera for the [Viewport] (see class description). If the Camera Node is outside the scene tree, it will attempt to become current once it's added.

methods.name: project_ray_normal
methods.description: Return a normal vector in worldspace, that is the result of projecting a point on the [Viewport] rectangle by the camera projection. This is useful for casting rays in the form of (origin,normal) for object intersection or picking.

methods.name: project_ray_origin
methods.description: Return a 3D position in worldspace, that is the result of projecting a point on the [Viewport] rectangle by the camera projection. This is useful for casting rays in the form of (origin,normal) for object intersection or picking.

methods.name: set_orthogonal
methods.description: Set the camera projection to orthogonal mode, by specifying a width and the [i]near[/i] and [i]far[/i] clip planes in worldspace units. (As a hint, 2D games often use this projection, with values specified in pixels)

methods.name: set_perspective
methods.description: Set the camera projection to perspective mode, by specifying a [i]FOV[/i] Y angle in degrees (FOV means Field of View), and the [i]near[/i] and [i]far[/i] clip planes in worldspace units.

methods.name: unproject_position
methods.description: Return how a 3D point in worldspace maps to a 2D coordinate in the [Viewport] rectangle.

constants.name: PROJECTION_PERSPECTIVE
constants.description: Perspective Projection (object's size on the screen becomes smaller when far away).

constants.name: PROJECTION_ORTHOGONAL
constants.description: Orthogonal Projection (objects remain the same size on the screen no matter how far away they are).

Camera2D.name: Camera2D
Camera2D.description:
Camera node for 2D scenes. It forces the screen (current layer) to scroll following this node. This makes it easier (and faster) to program scrollable scenes than manually changing the position of [CanvasItem] based nodes.
		This node is intended to be a simple helper get get things going quickly and it may happen often that more functionality is desired to change how the camera works. To make your own custom camera node, simply inherit from [Node2D] and change the transform of the canvas by calling get_viewport().set_canvas_transform(m) in [Viewport].

methods.name: align
methods.description: Align the camera to the tracked node

methods.name: force_update_scroll
methods.description: Force the camera to update scroll immediately.

methods.name: get_camera_pos
methods.description: Return the camera position.

methods.name: get_drag_margin
methods.description: Return the margins needed to drag the camera (see [method set_drag_margin]).

methods.name: get_limit
methods.description: Return the scrolling limit in pixels.

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return the scroll offset.

methods.name: is_current
methods.description: Return true of this is the current camera (see [method make_current]).

methods.name: make_current
methods.description: Make this the current 2D camera for the scene (viewport and layer), in case there's many cameras in the scene.

methods.name: reset_smoothing
methods.description:
Set the camera's position immediately to its current smoothing destination.
				This has no effect if smoothing is disabled.

methods.name: set_drag_margin
methods.description: Set the margins needed to drag the camera (relative to the screen size). Margin uses the MARGIN_* enum. Drag margins of 0,0,0,0 will keep the camera at the center of the screen, while drag margins of 1,1,1,1 will only move when the camera is at the edges.

methods.name: set_limit
methods.description: Set the scrolling limit in pixels.

methods.name: set_limit_smoothing_enabled
methods.description:
Smooth camera when reaching camera limits.
				This requires camera smoothing being enabled to have a noticeable effect.

methods.name: set_offset
methods.description: Set the scroll offset. Useful for looking around or camera shake animations.

CanvasItem.name: CanvasItem
CanvasItem.description:
Base class of anything 2D. Canvas items are laid out in a tree and children inherit and extend the transform of their parent. CanvasItem is extended by [Control], for anything GUI related, and by [Node2D] for anything 2D engine related.
		Any CanvasItem can draw. For this, the "update" function must be called, then NOTIFICATION_DRAW will be received on idle time to request redraw. Because of this, canvas items don't need to be redraw on every frame, improving the performance significantly. Several functions for drawing on the CanvasItem are provided (see draw_* functions). They can only be used inside the notification, signal or _draw() overrides function, though.
		Canvas items are draw in tree order. By default, children are on top of their parents so a root CanvasItem will be drawn behind everything (this can be changed per item though).
		Canvas items can also be hidden (hiding also their subtree). They provide many means for changing standard parameters such as opacity (for it and the subtree) and self opacity, blend mode.
		Ultimately, a transform notification can be requested, which will notify the node that its global position changed in case the parent tree changed.

methods.name: _draw
methods.description: Called (if exists) to draw the canvas item.

methods.name: draw_char
methods.description: Draw a string character using a custom font. Returns the advance, depending on the char width and kerning with an optional next char.

methods.name: draw_circle
methods.description: Draw a colored circle.

methods.name: draw_colored_polygon
methods.description: Draw a colored polygon of any amount of points, convex or concave.

methods.name: draw_line
methods.description: Draw a line from a 2D point to another, with a given color and width. It can be optionally antialiased.

methods.name: draw_polygon
methods.description: Draw a polygon of any amount of points, convex or concave.

methods.name: draw_primitive
methods.description: Draw a custom primitive, 1 point for a point, 2 points for a line, 3 points for a triangle and 4 points for a quad.

methods.name: draw_rect
methods.description: Draw a colored rectangle.

methods.name: draw_set_transform
methods.description: Set a custom transform for drawing. Anything drawn afterwards will be transformed by this.

methods.name: draw_string
methods.description: Draw a string using a custom font.

methods.name: draw_style_box
methods.description: Draw a styled rectangle.

methods.name: draw_texture
methods.description: Draw a texture at a given position.

methods.name: draw_texture_rect
methods.description: Draw a textured rectangle at a given position, optionally modulated by a color. Transpose swaps the x and y coordinates when reading the texture.

methods.name: draw_texture_rect_region
methods.description: Draw a textured rectangle region at a given position, optionally modulated by a color. Transpose swaps the x and y coordinates when reading the texture.

methods.name: edit_get_state
methods.description: Used for editing, returns an opaque value representing the transform state.

methods.name: edit_rotate
methods.description: Used for editing, handle rotation.

methods.name: edit_set_state
methods.description: Set the transform state of this CanvasItem. For [Node2D], this is an [Array] with (in order) a [Vector2] for position, a float for rotation (radians) and another [Vector2] for scale. For [Control] this is a [Rect2] with the position and size.

methods.name: get_canvas
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the [World2D] canvas where this item is in.

methods.name: get_canvas_item
methods.description: Return the canvas item RID used by [VisualServer] for this item.

methods.name: get_canvas_transform
methods.description: Get the transform matrix of this item's canvas.

methods.name: get_global_mouse_position
methods.description: Get the global position of the mouse.

methods.name: get_global_transform
methods.description: Get the global transform matrix of this item.

methods.name: get_global_transform_with_canvas
methods.description: Get the global transform matrix of this item in relation to the canvas.

methods.name: get_item_and_children_rect
methods.description: Get a [Rect2] with the boundaries of this item and its children.

methods.name: get_item_rect
methods.description: Return a rect containing the editable boundaries of the item.

methods.name: get_light_mask
methods.description: Get this item's light mask number.

methods.name: get_local_mouse_pos
methods.description: Get the mouse position relative to this item's position.

methods.name: get_material
methods.description: Get the material of this item.

methods.name: get_modulate
methods.description: Get the modulate of the CanvasItem, which affects children items too.

methods.name: get_self_modulate
methods.description: Get the self-modulate of the CanvasItem.

methods.name: get_transform
methods.description: Get the transform matrix of this item.

methods.name: get_use_parent_material
methods.description: Get whether this item uses its parent's material.

methods.name: get_viewport_rect
methods.description: Get the viewport's boundaries as a [Rect2].

methods.name: get_viewport_transform
methods.description: Get this item's transform in relation to the viewport.

methods.name: get_world_2d
methods.description: Get the [World2D] where this item is in.

methods.name: hide
methods.description: Hide the CanvasItem currently visible.

methods.name: is_draw_behind_parent_enabled
methods.description: Return whether the item is drawn behind its parent.

methods.name: is_set_as_toplevel
methods.description: Return if set as toplevel. See [method set_as_toplevel].

methods.name: is_visible
methods.description: Return true if this CanvasItem is visible. It may be invisible because itself or a parent canvas item is hidden.

methods.name: set_as_toplevel
methods.description: Set as top level. This means that it will not inherit transform from parent canvas items.

methods.name: set_draw_behind_parent
methods.description: Set whether the canvas item is drawn behind its parent.

methods.name: set_light_mask
methods.description: Set the ligtht mask number of this item.

methods.name: set_material
methods.description: Set the material of this item.

methods.name: set_modulate
methods.description: Set the modulate of the CanvasItem. This [i]affects[/i] the modulation of children items.

methods.name: set_self_modulate
methods.description: Set the self-modulate of the CanvasItem. This does not affect the modulation of children items.

methods.name: set_use_parent_material
methods.description: Set whether or not this item should use its parent's material.

methods.name: set_visible
methods.description:
Set whether this item should be visible or not.
				Note that a hidden CanvasItem will make all children hidden too, so no matter what is set here this item won't be shown if its parent or grandparents nodes are hidden.

methods.name: show
methods.description: Show the CanvasItem currently hidden.

methods.name: update
methods.description: Queue the CanvasItem for update. [code]NOTIFICATION_DRAW[/code] will be called on idle time to request redraw.

signals.name: draw
signals.description: Emitted when the CanvasItem must redraw. This can only be connected realtime, as deferred will not allow drawing.

signals.name: hide
signals.description: Emitted when becoming hidden.

signals.name: item_rect_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the item rect has changed.

signals.name: visibility_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the visibility (hidden/visible) changes.

constants.name: BLEND_MODE_MIX
constants.description: Mix blending mode. Colors are assumed to be independent of the alpha (opacity) value.

constants.name: BLEND_MODE_PREMULT_ALPHA
constants.description: Mix blending mode. Colors are assumed to be premultiplied by the alpha (opacity) value.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_ENTER_CANVAS
constants.description: Canvas item has entered the canvas.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_EXIT_CANVAS
constants.description: Canvas item has exited the canvas.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_TRANSFORM_CHANGED
constants.description: Canvas item transform has changed. Only received if requested.

CanvasLayer.name: CanvasLayer
CanvasLayer.description: Canvas Item layer. [CanvasItem] nodes that are direct or indirect children of a [CanvasLayer] will be drawn in that layer. The layer is a numeric index that defines the draw order. The default 2D scene renders with index 0, so a [CanvasLayer] with index -1 will be drawn below, and one with index 1 will be drawn above. This is very useful for HUDs (in layer 1+ or above), or backgrounds (in layer -1 or below).

methods.name: get_layer
methods.description: Return the layer index, determines the draw order, a lower value will be below a higher one.

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return the base offset for this layer (helper).

methods.name: get_rotation
methods.description: Return the base rotation for this layer in radians (helper).

methods.name: get_rotationd
methods.description: Return the base rotation for this layer in degrees.

methods.name: get_scale
methods.description: Return the base scale for this layer (helper).

methods.name: get_transform
methods.description: Return the base transform for this layer.

methods.name: get_world_2d
methods.description: Return the [World2D] used by this layer.

methods.name: set_layer
methods.description: Set the layer index, determines the draw order, a lower value will be below a higher one.

methods.name: set_offset
methods.description: Set the base offset for this layer (helper).

methods.name: set_rotation
methods.description: Set the base rotation for this layer in radians (helper).

methods.name: set_rotationd
methods.description: Set the base rotation for this layer in degrees (helper).

methods.name: set_scale
methods.description: Set the base scale for this layer (helper).

methods.name: set_transform
methods.description: Set the base transform for this layer.

CanvasModulate.name: CanvasModulate
CanvasModulate.description: CanvasModulate tints the canvas elements using its assigned color

methods.name: get_color
methods.description: Gets the canvas tint color

methods.name: set_color
methods.description: Sets the canvas tint color

CapsuleShape.name: CapsuleShape
CapsuleShape.description: Capsule shape resource, which can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or area.

methods.name: get_height
methods.description: Return the capsule height.

methods.name: get_radius
methods.description: Return the capsule radius.

methods.name: set_height
methods.description: Set the capsule height.

methods.name: set_radius
methods.description: Set the capsule radius.

CapsuleShape2D.name: CapsuleShape2D
CapsuleShape2D.description: Capsule 2D shape resource for physics. A capsule (or sometimes called "pill") is like a line grown in all directions. It has a radius and a height, and is often useful for modeling biped characters.

methods.name: get_height
methods.description: Return the height of the [CapsuleShape2D].

methods.name: get_radius
methods.description: Return the radius of the [CapsuleShape2D].

methods.name: set_height
methods.description: Set the height of the [CapsuleShape2D].

methods.name: set_radius
methods.description: Set the radius of the [CapsuleShape2D].

CenterContainer.name: CenterContainer
CenterContainer.description: CenterContainer Keeps children controls centered. This container keeps all children to their minimum size, in the center.

methods.name: is_using_top_left
methods.description: Should put children to the top left corner instead of center of the container.

methods.name: set_use_top_left
methods.description: This function will anchor the container children to the top left corner of the the container boundaries, moving all its children to that position, (the children new center will be the top left corner of the container).

CheckBox.name: CheckBox
CheckBox.description: A checkbox allows the user to make a binary choice (choosing only one of two posible options), for example Answer 'yes' or 'no'.

CheckButton.name: CheckButton
CheckButton.description: CheckButton is a toggle button displayed as a check field.

CircleShape2D.name: CircleShape2D
CircleShape2D.description: Circular Shape for 2D Physics. This shape is useful for modeling balls or small characters and its collision detection with everything else is very fast.

methods.name: get_radius
methods.description: Return the radius of the circle shape.

methods.name: set_radius
methods.description: Set the radius of the circle shape.

methods.name: create_shape_owner
methods.description: Creates new holder for the shapes. Argument is a [CollisionShape] node. It will return owner_id which usually you will want to save for later use.

methods.name: get_shape_owners
methods.description: Shape owner is a node which is holding concrete shape resources. This method will return an array which is holding an integer numbers that are representing unique ID of each owner. You can use those ids when you are using others shape_owner methods.

methods.name: shape_owner_clear_shapes
methods.description: Will remove all the shapes associated with given owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape
methods.description: Will return a [Shape]. First argument owner_id is an integer that can be obtained from [method get_shape_owners]. Shape_id is a position of the shape inside owner; it's a value in range from 0 to [method shape_owner_get_shape_count].

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape_count
methods.description: Returns number of shapes to which given owner is associated to.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_transform
methods.description: Will return [Transform] of an owner node.

methods.name: shape_owner_remove_shape
methods.description: Removes related shape from the owner.

CollisionObject2D.name: CollisionObject2D
CollisionObject2D.description: CollisionObject2D is the base class for 2D physics collisionables. They can hold any number of 2D collision shapes. Usually, they are edited by placing [CollisionShape2D] and/or [CollisionPolygon2D] nodes as children. Such nodes are for reference and not present outside the editor, so code should use the regular shape API.

methods.name: create_shape_owner
methods.description: Creates new holder for the shapes. Argument is a [CollisionShape2D] node. It will return owner_id which usually you will want to save for later use.

methods.name: get_rid
methods.description: Return the RID of this object.

methods.name: get_shape_owners
methods.description: Shape owner is a node which is holding concrete shape resources. This method will return an array which is holding an integer numbers that are representing unique ID of each owner. You can use those ids when you are using others shape_owner methods.

methods.name: shape_owner_clear_shapes
methods.description: Will remove all the shapes associated with given owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape
methods.description: Will return a [Shape2D]. First argument owner_id is an integer that can be obtained from [method get_shape_owners]. Shape_id is a position of the shape inside owner; it's a value in range from 0 to [method shape_owner_get_shape_count].

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape_count
methods.description: Returns number of shapes to which given owner is associated to.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_transform
methods.description: Will return [Transform2D] of an owner node.

methods.name: shape_owner_remove_shape

ConcavePolygonShape2D.name: ConcavePolygonShape2D
ConcavePolygonShape2D.brief_description: Concave polygon 2D shape resource for physics.
ConcavePolygonShape2D.description:
Concave polygon 2D shape resource for physics. It is made out of segments and is very optimal for complex polygonal concave collisions. It is really not advised to use for [RigidBody2D] nodes. A CollisionPolygon2D in convex decomposition mode (solids) or several convex objects are advised for that instead. Otherwise, a concave polygon 2D shape is better for static collisions.
		The main difference between a [ConvexPolygonShape2D] and a [ConcavePolygonShape2D] is that a concave polygon assumes it is concave and uses a more complex method of collision detection, and a convex one forces itself to be convex in order to speed up collision detection.

methods.name: get_segments
methods.description: Return the array of segments.

methods.name: set_segments
methods.description: Set the array of segments.

ConfigFile.name: ConfigFile
ConfigFile.brief_description: Helper class to handle INI-style files.
ConfigFile.description:
This helper class can be used to store [Variant] values on the filesystem using an INI-style formatting. The stored values as referenced by a section and a key. The stored data can be saved to or parsed from a file, though ConfigFile objects can also be used directly with accessing the filesystem.
		The following example shows how to parse a INI-style file from the system, read its contents and store new values in it:
		[codeblock]
		var config = ConfigFile.new()
		var err = config.load("user://settings.cfg")
		if err == OK: # if not, something went wrong with the file loading
		    # Look for the display/width pair, and default to 1024 if missing
		    var screen_width = get_value("display", "width", 1024)
		    # Store a variable if and only it hasn't been defined yet
		    if not config.has_section_key("audio", "mute"):
		        config.set_value("audio", "mute", false)
		    # Save the changes by overwriting the previous file
		    config.save("user://settings.cfg")
		[/codeblock]

methods.name: get_section_keys
methods.description: Return an array of all defined key identifiers in the specified section.

methods.name: get_sections
methods.description: Return an array of all defined section identifiers.

methods.name: get_value
methods.description: Return the current value for the specified section and key. If the section and/or the key do not exist, the method returns the value of the optional [i]default[/i] argument (and thus [code]NULL[/code] if not specified).

methods.name: has_section
methods.description: Check if the specified section exists.

methods.name: has_section_key
methods.description: Check if the specified section-key pair exists.

methods.name: load
methods.description: Load the config file specified as a parameter. The file's contents are parsed and loaded in the ConfigFile object from which the method was called. The return value is one of the OK, FAILED or ERR_* constants listed in [@Global Scope] (if the load was successful, it returns OK).

methods.name: save
methods.description:
Save the contents of the ConfigFile object to the file specified as a parameter. The output file uses an INI-style structure.
				The return value is one of the OK, FAILED or ERR_* constants listed in [@Global Scope] (if the save was successful, it returns OK).

methods.name: set_value
methods.description: Assign a value to the specified key of the the specified section. If the section and/or the key do not exist, they are created. Passing a [code]NULL[/code] value deletes the specified key if it exists (and deletes the section if it ends up empty once the key has been removed).

Container.name: Container
Container.description:
Base node for containers. A [Container] contains other controls and automatically arranges them in a certain way.
		A Control can inherit this to create custom container classes.

Control.name: Control
Control.brief_description: Control is the base node for all the GUI components.
Control.description:
Control is the base class Node for all the GUI components. Every GUI component inherits from it, directly or indirectly. In this way, sections of the scene tree made of contiguous control nodes, become user interfaces.
		Controls are relative to the parent position and size by using anchors and margins. This ensures that they can adapt easily in most situation to changing dialog and screen sizes. When more flexibility is desired, [Container] derived nodes can be used.
		Anchors work by defining which margin do they follow, and a value relative to it. Allowed anchoring modes are ANCHOR_BEGIN, where the margin is relative to the top or left margins of the parent (in pixels), ANCHOR_END for the right and bottom margins of the parent and ANCHOR_RATIO, which is a ratio from 0 to 1 in the parent range.
		Input device events are first sent to the root controls via the [method Node._input], which distribute it through the tree, then delivers them to the adequate one (under cursor or keyboard focus based) by calling [method MainLoop._input_event]. There is no need to enable input processing on controls to receive such events. To ensure that no one else will receive the event (not even [method Node._unhandled_input]), the control can accept it by calling [method accept_event].
		Only one control can hold the keyboard focus (receiving keyboard events), for that the control must define the focus mode with [method set_focus_mode]. Focus is lost when another control gains it, or the current focus owner is hidden.
		It is sometimes desired for a control to ignore mouse/pointer events. This is often the case when placing other controls on top of a button, in such cases. Calling [method set_ignore_mouse] enables this function.
		Finally, controls are skinned according to a [Theme]. Setting a [Theme] on a control will propagate all the skinning down the tree. Optionally, skinning can be overridden per each control by calling the add_*_override functions, or from the editor.

methods.name: _get_minimum_size
methods.description: Return the minimum size this Control can shrink to. A control will never be displayed or resized smaller than its minimum size.

methods.name: accept_event
methods.description: Handles the event, no other control will receive it and it will not be sent to nodes waiting on [method Node._unhandled_input] or [method Node._unhandled_key_input].

methods.name: add_constant_override
methods.description: Override a single constant (integer) in the theme of this Control. If constant equals Theme.INVALID_CONSTANT, override is cleared.

methods.name: add_font_override
methods.description: Override a single font (font) in the theme of this Control. If font is empty, override is cleared.

methods.name: add_icon_override
methods.description: Override a single icon ([Texture]) in the theme of this Control. If texture is empty, override is cleared.

methods.name: add_style_override
methods.description: Override a single stylebox ([Stylebox]) in the theme of this Control. If stylebox is empty, override is cleared.

methods.name: get_anchor
methods.description: Return the anchor type (ANCHOR_BEGIN, ANCHOR_END, ANCHOR_RATIO) for a given margin (MARGIN_LEFT, MARGIN_TOP, MARGIN_RIGHT, MARGIN_BOTTOM).

methods.name: get_cursor_shape
methods.description: Return the cursor shape at a certain position in the control.

methods.name: get_default_cursor_shape
methods.description: Return the default cursor shape for this control. See enum CURSOR_* for the list of shapes.

methods.name: get_end
methods.description: Returns MARGIN_LEFT and MARGIN_TOP at the same time. This is a helper (see [method set_margin]).

methods.name: get_focus_mode
methods.description: Returns the focus access mode for the control (FOCUS_NONE, FOCUS_CLICK, FOCUS_ALL) (see [method set_focus_mode]).

methods.name: get_focus_neighbour
methods.description: Return the forced neighbour for moving the input focus to. When pressing TAB or directional/joypad directions focus is moved to the next control in that direction. However, the neighbour to move to can be forced with this function.

methods.name: get_focus_owner
methods.description: Return which control is owning the keyboard focus, or null if no one.

methods.name: get_global_position
methods.description: Returns the Control position, relative to the top-left corner of the parent Control and independent of the anchor mode.

methods.name: get_global_rect
methods.description: Return position and size of the Control, relative to the top-left corner of the [i]window[/i] Control. This is a helper (see [method get_global_position], [method get_size]).

methods.name: get_h_size_flags
methods.description: Hint for containers, return horizontal positioning flags.

methods.name: get_margin
methods.description: Return a margin offset. Margin can be one of (MARGIN_LEFT, MARGIN_TOP, MARGIN_RIGHT, MARGIN_BOTTOM). Offset value being returned depends on the anchor mode.

methods.name: get_minimum_size
methods.description: Return the minimum size this Control can shrink to. A control will never be displayed or resized smaller than its minimum size.

methods.name: get_mouse_filter
methods.description: Return when the control is ignoring mouse events (even touchpad events send mouse events).

methods.name: get_position
methods.description: Returns the Control position, relative to the top-left corner of the parent Control and independent of the anchor mode.

methods.name: get_rect
methods.description: Return position and size of the Control, relative to the top-left corner of the parent Control. This is a helper (see [method get_position], [method get_size]).

methods.name: get_rotation
methods.description: Return the rotation (in radians)

methods.name: get_rotation_deg
methods.description: Return the rotation (in degrees)

methods.name: get_size
methods.description: Returns the size of the Control, computed from all margins, however the size returned will [b]never be smaller than the minimum size reported by[/b] [method get_minimum_size]. This means that even if end position of the Control rectangle is smaller than the begin position, the Control will still display and interact correctly. (see description, [method get_minimum_size], [method set_margin], [method set_anchor]).

methods.name: get_stretch_ratio
methods.description: Hint for containers, return the stretch ratio. This value is relative to other stretch ratio, so if this control has 2 and another has 1, this one will be twice as big.

methods.name: get_theme
methods.description: Return a [Theme] override, if one exists (see [method set_theme]).

methods.name: get_tooltip
methods.description: Return the tooltip, which will appear when the cursor is resting over this control.

methods.name: get_v_size_flags
methods.description: Hint for containers, return vertical positioning flags.

methods.name: grab_focus
methods.description: Steal the focus from another control and become the focused control (see [method set_focus_mode]).

methods.name: has_focus
methods.description: Return whether the Control is the current focused control (see [method set_focus_mode]).

methods.name: release_focus
methods.description: Give up the focus, no other control will be able to receive keyboard input.

methods.name: set_anchor
methods.description:
Change the anchor (ANCHOR_BEGIN, ANCHOR_END, ANCHOR_RATIO) type for a margin (MARGIN_LEFT, MARGIN_TOP, MARGIN_RIGHT, MARGIN_BOTTOM). Changing the anchor mode converts the current margin offset from the previous anchor mode to the new one, so margin offsets ([method set_margin]) must be done after setting anchors, or at the same time ([method set_anchor_and_margin])
				Additionally, [code]keep_margin[/code] controls whether margins should be left the same, or changed to keep the same position and size on-screen.

methods.name: set_anchor_and_margin
methods.description: Change the anchor (ANCHOR_BEGIN, ANCHOR_END, ANCHOR_RATIO) type for a margin (MARGIN_LEFT, MARGIN_TOP, MARGIN_RIGHT, MARGIN_BOTTOM), and also set its offset. This is a helper (see [method set_anchor] and [method set_margin]).

methods.name: set_area_as_parent_rect
methods.description: Change all margins and anchors, so this Control always takes up the same area as the parent Control. This is a helper (see [method set_anchor], [method set_margin]).

methods.name: set_begin
methods.description: Sets MARGIN_LEFT and MARGIN_TOP at the same time. This is a helper (see [method set_margin]).

methods.name: set_default_cursor_shape
methods.description: Set the default cursor shape for this control. See enum CURSOR_* for the list of shapes.

methods.name: set_end
methods.description: Sets MARGIN_RIGHT and MARGIN_BOTTOM at the same time. This is a helper (see [method set_margin]).

methods.name: set_focus_mode
methods.description: Set the focus access mode for the control (FOCUS_NONE, FOCUS_CLICK, FOCUS_ALL). Only one Control can be focused at the same time, and it will receive keyboard signals.

methods.name: set_focus_neighbour
methods.description: Force a neighbour for moving the input focus to. When pressing TAB or directional/joypad directions focus is moved to the next control in that direction. However, the neighbour to move to can be forced with this function.

methods.name: set_global_position
methods.description: Move the Control to a new position, relative to the top-left corner of the [i]window[/i] Control, and without changing current anchor mode. (see [method set_margin]).

methods.name: set_h_size_flags
methods.description: Hint for containers, set horizontal positioning flags.

methods.name: set_margin
methods.description: Set a margin offset. Margin can be one of (MARGIN_LEFT, MARGIN_TOP, MARGIN_RIGHT, MARGIN_BOTTOM). Offset value being set depends on the anchor mode.

methods.name: set_mouse_filter
methods.description: Set when the control is ignoring mouse events (even touchpad events send mouse events). (see the MOUSE_FILTER_* constants)

methods.name: set_position
methods.description: Move the Control to a new position, relative to the top-left corner of the parent Control, changing all margins if needed and without changing current anchor mode. This is a helper (see [method set_margin]).

methods.name: set_rotation
methods.description: Set the rotation (in radians).

methods.name: set_rotation_deg
methods.description: Set the rotation (in degrees).

methods.name: set_size
methods.description: Changes MARGIN_RIGHT and MARGIN_BOTTOM to fit a given size. This is a helper (see [method set_margin]).

methods.name: set_stretch_ratio
methods.description: Hint for containers, set the stretch ratio. This value is relative to other stretch ratio, so if this control has 2 and another has 1, this one will be twice as big.

methods.name: set_theme
methods.description: Override whole the [Theme] for this Control and all its children controls.

methods.name: set_tooltip
methods.description: Set a tooltip, which will appear when the cursor is resting over this control.

methods.name: set_v_size_flags
methods.description: Hint for containers, set vertical positioning flags.

methods.name: show_modal
methods.description: Display a Control as modal. Control must be a subwindow. Modal controls capture the input signals until closed or the area outside them is accessed. When a modal control loses focus, or the ESC key is pressed, they automatically hide. Modal controls are used extensively for popup dialogs and menus.

signals.name: focus_entered
signals.description: Emitted when keyboard focus is gained.

signals.name: focus_exited
signals.description: Emitted when the keyboard focus is lost.

signals.name: minimum_size_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the minimum size of the control changed.

signals.name: mouse_entered
signals.description: Emitted when the mouse enters the control area.

signals.name: mouse_exited
signals.description: Emitted when the mouse left the control area.

signals.name: resized
signals.description: Emitted when the control changed size.

signals.name: size_flags_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the size flags changed.

constants.name: ANCHOR_BEGIN
constants.description: X is relative to MARGIN_LEFT, Y is relative to MARGIN_TOP.

constants.name: ANCHOR_END
constants.description: X is relative to -MARGIN_RIGHT, Y is relative to -MARGIN_BOTTOM.

constants.name: FOCUS_CLICK
constants.description: Control can acquire focus only if clicked.

constants.name: FOCUS_ALL
constants.description: Control can acquire focus if clicked, or by pressing TAB/Directionals in the keyboard from another Control.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_RESIZED
constants.description: Control changed size (get_size() reports the new size).

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_MOUSE_ENTER

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_MOUSE_EXIT
