methods.name: integrate_forces
methods.description: Call the built-in force integration code.

methods.name: is_sleeping
methods.description: Return true if this body is currently sleeping (not active).

methods.name: set_angular_velocity
methods.description: Change the angular velocity of the body.

methods.name: set_linear_velocity
methods.description: Change the linear velocity of the body.

methods.name: set_sleep_state
methods.description: Set the sleeping state of the body, only affects character/rigid bodies.

methods.name: set_transform
methods.description: Change the transform matrix of the body.

Physics2DDirectBodyStateSW.name: Physics2DDirectBodyStateSW
Physics2DDirectBodyStateSW.description: Software implementation of [Physics2DDirectBodyState]. This object exposes no new methods or properties and should not be used, as [Physics2DDirectBodyState] selects the best implementation available.

Physics2DDirectSpaceState.name: Physics2DDirectSpaceState
Physics2DDirectSpaceState.brief_description: Direct access object to a space in the [Physics2DServer].
Physics2DDirectSpaceState.description: Direct access object to a space in the [Physics2DServer]. It's used mainly to do queries against objects and areas residing in a given space.

methods.name: cast_motion
methods.description:
Check whether the shape can travel to a point. If it can, the method will return an array with two floats: The first is the distance the shape can move in that direction without colliding, and the second is the distance at which it will collide.
	If the shape can not move, the array will be empty.

methods.name: collide_shape
methods.description: Check the intersections of a shape, given through a [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. The resulting array contains a list of points where the shape intersects another. Like with [method intersect_shape], the number of returned results can be limited to save processing time.

methods.name: get_rest_info
methods.description:
Check the intersections of a shape, given through a [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. If it collides with more than a shape, the nearest one is selected. The returned object is a dictionary containing the following fields:
				pointo: Place where the shapes intersect.
				normal: Normal of the object at the point where the shapes intersect.
				shape: Shape index within the object against which the shape intersected.
				metadata: Metadata of the shape against which the shape intersected. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				collider_id: Id of the object against which the shape intersected.
				collider: Object against which the shape intersected.
				rid: [RID] of the object against which the shape intersected.
				linear_velocity: The movement vector of the object the shape intersected, if it was a body. If it was an area, it is (0,0).
				If the shape did not intersect anything, then an empty dictionary (dir.empty()==true) is returned instead.

methods.name: intersect_point
methods.description:
Check whether a point is inside any shape. The shapes the point is inside of are returned in an array containing dictionaries with the following fields:
				shape: Shape index within the object the point is in.
				metadata: Metadata of the shape the point is in. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				collider_id: Id of the object the point is in.
				collider: Object the point is inside of.
				rid: [RID] of the object the point is in.
				Additionally, the method can take an array of objects or [RID]\ s that are to be excluded from collisions, a bitmask representing the physics layers to check in, and another bitmask for the types of objects to check (see TYPE_MASK_* constants).

methods.name: intersect_ray
methods.description:
Intersect a ray in a given space. The returned object is a dictionary with the following fields:
				position: Place where ray is stopped.
				normal: Normal of the object at the point where the ray was stopped.
				shape: Shape index within the object against which the ray was stopped.
				metadata: Metadata of the shape against which the ray was stopped. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				collider_id: Id of the object against which the ray was stopped.
				collider: Object against which the ray was stopped.
				rid: [RID] of the object against which the ray was stopped.
				If the ray did not intersect anything, then an empty dictionary (dir.empty()==true) is returned instead.
				Additionally, the method can take an array of objects or [RID]\ s that are to be excluded from collisions, a bitmask representing the physics layers to check in, and another bitmask for the types of objects to check (see TYPE_MASK_* constants).

methods.name: intersect_shape
methods.description:
Check the intersections of a shape, given through a [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. The intersected shapes are returned in an array containing dictionaries with the following fields:
				shape: Shape index within the object the shape intersected.
				metadata: Metadata of the shape intersected by the shape given through the [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters]. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				collider_id: Id of the object the shape intersected.
				collider: Object the shape intersected.
				rid: [RID] of the object the shape intersected.
				The number of intersections can be limited with the second parameter, to reduce the processing time.

constants.name: TYPE_MASK_STATIC_BODY
constants.description: Check for collisions with static bodies.

constants.name: TYPE_MASK_KINEMATIC_BODY
constants.description: Check for collisions with kinematic bodies.

constants.name: TYPE_MASK_RIGID_BODY
constants.description: Check for collisions with rigid bodies.

constants.name: TYPE_MASK_CHARACTER_BODY
constants.description: Check for collisions with rigid bodies in character mode.

constants.name: TYPE_MASK_COLLISION
constants.description: Check for collisions with any kind of bodies (but not areas).

Physics2DServer.name: Physics2DServer
Physics2DServer.description: Physics 2D Server is the server responsible for all 2D physics. It can create many kinds of physics objects, but does not insert them on the node tree.

methods.name: area_add_shape
methods.description: Add a shape to the area, along with a transform matrix. Shapes are usually referenced by their index, so you should track which shape has a given index.

methods.name: area_attach_object_instance_ID
methods.description: Assign the area to a descendant of [Object], so it can exist in the node tree.

methods.name: area_clear_shapes
methods.description: Remove all shapes from an area. It does not delete the shapes, so they can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_create
methods.description: Create an [Area2D].

methods.name: area_get_object_instance_ID
methods.description: Get the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: area_get_param
methods.description: Return an area parameter value.

methods.name: area_get_shape
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the nth shape of an area.

methods.name: area_get_shape_count
methods.description: Return the number of shapes assigned to an area.

methods.name: area_get_shape_transform
methods.description: Return the transform matrix of a shape within an area.

methods.name: area_get_space
methods.description: Return the space assigned to the area.

methods.name: area_get_space_override_mode
methods.description: Return the space override mode for the area.

methods.name: area_get_transform
methods.description: Return the transform matrix for an area.

methods.name: area_remove_shape
methods.description: Remove a shape from an area. It does not delete the shape, so it can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_set_collision_layer
methods.description: Assign the area to one or many physics layers.

methods.name: area_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Set which physics layers the area will monitor.

methods.name: area_set_monitor_callback
methods.description:
Set the function to call when any body/area enters or exits the area. This callback will be called for any object interacting with the area, and takes five parameters:
				1: AREA_BODY_ADDED or AREA_BODY_REMOVED, depending on whether the object entered or exited the area.
				2: [RID] of the object that entered/exited the area.
				3: Instance ID of the object that entered/exited the area.
				4: The shape index of the object that entered/exited the area.
				5: The shape index of the area where the object entered/exited.

methods.name: area_set_param
methods.description: Set the value for an area parameter. A list of available parameters is on the AREA_PARAM_* constants.

methods.name: area_set_shape
methods.description: Substitute a given area shape by another. The old shape is selected by its index, the new one by its [RID].

methods.name: area_set_shape_transform
methods.description: Set the transform matrix for an area shape.

methods.name: area_set_space
methods.description: Assign a space to the area.

methods.name: area_set_space_override_mode
methods.description: Set the space override mode for the area. The modes are described in the constants AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_*.

methods.name: area_set_transform
methods.description: Set the transform matrix for an area.

methods.name: body_add_collision_exception
methods.description: Add a body to the list of bodies exempt from collisions.

methods.name: body_add_force
methods.description: Add a positioned force to the applied force and torque. As with [method body_apply_impulse], both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates. A force differs from an impulse in that, while the two are forces, the impulse clears itself after being applied.

methods.name: body_add_shape
methods.description: Add a shape to the body, along with a transform matrix. Shapes are usually referenced by their index, so you should track which shape has a given index.

methods.name: body_apply_impulse
methods.description: Add a positioned impulse to the applied force and torque. Both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: body_attach_object_instance_ID
methods.description: Assign the area to a descendant of [Object], so it can exist in the node tree.

methods.name: body_clear_shapes
methods.description: Remove all shapes from a body.

methods.name: body_create
methods.description: Create a physics body. The first parameter can be any value from constants BODY_MODE*, for the type of body created. Additionally, the body can be created in sleeping state to save processing time.

methods.name: body_get_collision_layer
methods.description: Return the physics layer or layers a body belongs to.

methods.name: body_get_collision_mask
methods.description: Return the physics layer or layers a body can collide with.

methods.name: body_get_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description: Return the continuous collision detection mode.

methods.name: body_get_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Return the maximum contacts that can be reported. See [method body_set_max_contacts_reported].

methods.name: body_get_mode
methods.description: Return the body mode.

methods.name: body_get_object_instance_ID
methods.description: Get the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: body_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a body parameter.

methods.name: body_get_shape
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the nth shape of a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_count
methods.description: Return the number of shapes assigned to a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_metadata
methods.description: Return the metadata of a shape of a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_transform
methods.description: Return the transform matrix of a body shape.

methods.name: body_get_space
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the space assigned to a body.

methods.name: body_get_state
methods.description: Return a body state.

methods.name: body_is_omitting_force_integration
methods.description: Return whether a body uses a callback function to calculate its own physics (see [method body_set_force_integration_callback]).

methods.name: body_remove_collision_exception
methods.description: Remove a body from the list of bodies exempt from collisions.

methods.name: body_remove_shape
methods.description: Remove a shape from a body. The shape is not deleted, so it can be reused afterwards.

methods.name: body_set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Set an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: body_set_collision_layer
methods.description: Set the physics layer or layers a body belongs to.

methods.name: body_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Set the physics layer or layers a body can collide with.

methods.name: body_set_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description:
Set the continuous collision detection mode from any of the CCD_MODE_* constants.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided.

methods.name: body_set_force_integration_callback
methods.description: Set the function used to calculate physics for an object, if that object allows it (see [method body_set_omit_force integration]).

methods.name: body_set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Set the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: body_set_mode
methods.description: Set the body mode, from one of the constants BODY_MODE*.

methods.name: body_set_omit_force_integration
methods.description: Set whether a body uses a callback function to calculate its own physics (see [method body_set_force_integration_callback]).

methods.name: body_set_param
methods.description: Set a body parameter (see BODY_PARAM* constants).

methods.name: body_set_shape
methods.description: Substitute a given body shape by another. The old shape is selected by its index, the new one by its [RID].

methods.name: body_set_shape_metadata
methods.description: Set metadata of a shape within a body. This metadata is different from [method Object.set_meta], and can be retrieved on shape queries.

methods.name: body_set_shape_transform
methods.description: Set the transform matrix for a body shape.

methods.name: body_set_space
methods.description: Assign a space to the body (see [method create_space]).

methods.name: body_set_state
methods.description: Set a body state (see BODY_STATE* constants).

methods.name: body_test_motion
methods.description: Return whether a body can move from a given point in a given direction. Apart from the boolean return value, a [Physics2DTestMotionResult] can be passed to return additional information in.

methods.name: damped_spring_joint_create
methods.description: Create a damped spring joint between two bodies. If not specified, the second body is assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: damped_string_joint_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a damped spring joint parameter.

methods.name: damped_string_joint_set_param
methods.description: Set a damped spring joint parameter. Parameters are explained in the DAMPED_STRING* constants.

methods.name: free_rid
methods.description: Destroy any of the objects created by Physics2DServer. If the [RID] passed is not one of the objects that can be created by Physics2DServer, an error will be sent to the console.

methods.name: get_process_info
methods.description: Return information about the current state of the 2D physics engine. The states are listed under the INFO_* constants.

methods.name: groove_joint_create
methods.description: Create a groove joint between two bodies. If not specified, the bodyies are assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: joint_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a joint parameter.

methods.name: joint_get_type
methods.description: Return the type of a joint (see JOINT_* constants).

methods.name: joint_set_param
methods.description: Set a joint parameter. Parameters are explained in the JOINT_PARAM* constants.

methods.name: pin_joint_create
methods.description: Create a pin joint between two bodies. If not specified, the second body is assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: set_active
methods.description: Activate or deactivate the 2D physics engine.

methods.name: shape_create
methods.description: Create a shape of type SHAPE_*. Does not assign it to a body or an area. To do so, you must use [method area_set_shape] or [method body_set_shape].

methods.name: shape_get_data
methods.description: Return the shape data.

methods.name: shape_get_type
methods.description: Return the type of shape (see SHAPE_* constants).

methods.name: shape_set_data
methods.description: Set the shape data that defines its shape and size. The data to be passed depends on the kind of shape created [method shape_get_type].

methods.name: space_create
methods.description: Create a space. A space is a collection of parameters for the physics engine that can be assigned to an area or a body. It can be assigned to an area with [method area_set_space], or to a body with [method body_set_space].

methods.name: space_get_direct_state
methods.description: Return the state of a space, a [Physics2DDirectSpaceState]. This object can be used to make collision/intersection queries.

methods.name: space_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a space parameter.

methods.name: space_is_active
methods.description: Return whether the space is active.

methods.name: space_set_active
methods.description: Mark a space as active. It will not have an effect, unless it is assigned to an area or body.

methods.name: space_set_param
methods.description: Set the value for a space parameter. A list of available parameters is on the SPACE_PARAM_* constants.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_RECYCLE_RADIUS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a pair of bodies has to move before their collision status has to be recalculated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_MAX_SEPARATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can be from another before they are considered separated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_MAX_ALLOWED_PENETRATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can penetrate another shape before it is considered a collision.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_TIME_TO_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum time of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after this time.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONSTRAINT_DEFAULT_BIAS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the default solver bias for all physics constraints. A solver bias is a factor controlling how much two objects "rebound", after violating a constraint, to avoid leaving them in that state because of numerical imprecision.

constants.name: SHAPE_LINE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating line shapes. A line shape is an infinite line with an origin point, and a normal. Thus, it can be used for front/behind checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_SEGMENT
constants.description: This is the constant for creating segment shapes. A segment shape is a line from a point A to a point B. It can be checked for intersections.

constants.name: SHAPE_CIRCLE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating circle shapes. A circle shape only has a radius. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_RECTANGLE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating rectangle shapes. A rectangle shape is defined by a width and a height. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CAPSULE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating capsule shapes. A capsule shape is defined by a radius and a length. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CONVEX_POLYGON
constants.description: This is the constant for creating convex polygon shapes. A polygon is defined by a list of points. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks. Unlike the method [method CollisionPolygon2D.set_polygon], polygons modified with [method shape_set_data] do not verify that the points supplied form, in fact, a convex polygon.

constants.name: SHAPE_CONCAVE_POLYGON
constants.description: This is the constant for creating concave polygon shapes. A polygon is defined by a list of points. It can be used for intersections checks, but not for inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CUSTOM
constants.description: This constant is used internally by the engine. Any attempt to create this kind of shape results in an error.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get gravity strength in an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_VECTOR
constants.description: Constant to set/get gravity vector/center in an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_IS_POINT
constants.description: Constant to set/get whether the gravity vector of an area is a direction, or a center point.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity of an area. The greater this value is, the faster the strength of gravity decreases with the square of distance.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_POINT_ATTENUATION
constants.description: This constant was used to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity. It has been superseded by AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the linear dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the angular dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_PRIORITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the priority (order of processing) of an area.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_DISABLED
constants.description: This area does not affect gravity/damp. These are generally areas that exist only to detect collisions, and objects entering or exiting them.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. This way, many overlapping areas can combine their physics to make interesting effects.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. Then stops taking into account the rest of the areas, even the default one.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp, even the default one, and stops taking into account the rest of the areas.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp calculated so far, but keeps calculating the rest of the areas, down to the default one.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Constant for rigid bodies in character mode. In this mode, a body can not rotate, and only its linear velocity is affected by physics.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_BOUNCE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's bounce factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_FRICTION
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's friction.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MASS
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's mass.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_INERTIA
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's inertia.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_GRAVITY_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's gravity multiplier.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's linear dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's angular dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MAX
constants.description: This is the last ID for body parameters. Any attempt to set this property is ignored. Any attempt to get it returns 0.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_TRANSFORM
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current transform matrix of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_LINEAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current linear velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_ANGULAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current angular velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_SLEEPING
constants.description: Constant to sleep/wake up a body, or to get whether it is sleeping.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_CAN_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get whether the body can sleep.

constants.name: JOINT_DAMPED_SPRING
constants.description: Constant to create damped spring joints.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_REST_LENGTH
constants.description: Set the resting length of the spring joint. The joint will always try to go to back this length when pulled apart.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_STIFFNESS
constants.description: Set the stiffness of the spring joint. The joint applies a force equal to the stiffness times the distance from its resting length.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_DAMPING
constants.description: Set the damping ratio of the spring joint. A value of 0 indicates an undamped spring, while 1 causes the system to reach equilibrium as fast as possible (critical damping).

constants.name: CCD_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Disables continuous collision detection. This is the fastest way to detect body collisions, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_RAY
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by raycasting. It is faster than shapecasting, but less precise.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_SHAPE
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by shapecasting. It is the slowest CCD method, and the most precise.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_ADDED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object enters one of its shapes.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_REMOVED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object exits one of its shapes.

constants.name: INFO_ACTIVE_OBJECTS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of objects that are not sleeping.

constants.name: INFO_COLLISION_PAIRS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of possible collisions.

constants.name: INFO_ISLAND_COUNT
constants.description: Constant to get the number of space regions where a collision could occur.

Physics2DServerSW.name: Physics2DServerSW
Physics2DServerSW.description: Software implementation of [Physics2DServer]. This class exposes no new methods or properties and should not be used, as [Physics2DServer] automatically selects the best implementation available.

Physics2DShapeQueryParameters.name: Physics2DShapeQueryParameters
Physics2DShapeQueryParameters.brief_description: Parameters to be sent to a 2D shape physics query.
Physics2DShapeQueryParameters.description: This class contains the shape and other parameters for intersection/collision queries.

methods.name: get_collision_layer
methods.description: Return the physics layer the shape belongs to.

methods.name: get_exclude
methods.description: Return the list of objects, or object [RID]\ s, that will be excluded from collisions.

methods.name: get_margin
methods.description: Return the collision margin for the shape.

methods.name: get_motion
methods.description: Return the current movement speed of the shape.

methods.name: get_object_type_mask
methods.description: Return the type of object the shape belongs to.

methods.name: get_shape_rid
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the shape queried.

methods.name: get_transform
methods.description: Return the transform matrix of the shape queried.

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description: Set the physics layer the shape belongs to.

methods.name: set_exclude
methods.description: Set the list of objects, or object [RID]\ s, that will be excluded from collisions.

methods.name: set_margin
methods.description: Set the collision margin for the shape. A collision margin is an amount (in pixels) that the shape will grow when computing collisions, to account for numerical imprecision.

methods.name: set_motion
methods.description: Set the current movement speed of the shape.

methods.name: set_object_type_mask
methods.description: Set the type of object the shape belongs to (see Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_*).

methods.name: set_shape
methods.description: Set the [Shape2D] that will be used for collision/intersection queries.

methods.name: set_shape_rid
methods.description: Set the [RID] of the shape to be used in queries.

methods.name: set_transform
methods.description: Set the transormation matrix of the shape. This is necessary to set its position/rotation/scale.

PhysicsBody.name: PhysicsBody
PhysicsBody.brief_description: Base class for different types of Physics bodies.
PhysicsBody.description: PhysicsBody is an abstract base class for implementing a physics body. All PhysicsBody types inherit from it.

PhysicsBody2D.name: PhysicsBody2D
PhysicsBody2D.brief_description: Base class for all objects affected by physics.
PhysicsBody2D.description: PhysicsBody2D is an abstract base class for implementing a physics body. All *Body2D types inherit from it.

methods.name: add_collision_exception_with
methods.description: Adds a body to the collision exception list. This list contains bodies that this body will not collide with.

methods.name: get_collision_layer
methods.description: Return the physics layer this area is in.

methods.name: get_collision_layer_bit
methods.description: Return an individual bit on the collision mask.

methods.name: get_collision_mask
methods.description: Return the physics layers this area can scan for collisions.

methods.name: get_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Return an individual bit on the collision mask.

methods.name: remove_collision_exception_with
methods.description: Removes a body from the collision exception list.

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description:
Set the physics layers this area is in.
				Collidable objects can exist in any of 32 different layers. These layers are not visual, but more of a tagging system instead. A collidable can use these layers/tags to select with which objects it can collide, using [method set_collision_mask].
				A contact is detected if object A is in any of the layers that object B scans, or object B is in any layer scanned by object A.

methods.name: set_collision_layer_bit
methods.description: Set/clear individual bits on the layer mask. This makes getting a body in/out of only one layer easier.

methods.name: set_collision_mask
methods.description: Set the physics layers this area can scan for collisions.

methods.name: set_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Set/clear individual bits on the collision mask. This makes selecting the areas scanned easier.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_DISABLED
constants.description: This area does not affect gravity/damp. These are generally areas that exist only to detect collisions, and objects entering or exiting them.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. This way, many overlapping areas can combine their physics to make interesting effects.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. Then stops taking into account the rest of the areas, even the default one.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp, even the default one, and stops taking into account the rest of the areas.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp calculated so far, but keeps calculating the rest of the areas, down to the default one.

PhysicsShapeQueryResult.name: PhysicsShapeQueryResult
PhysicsShapeQueryResult.brief_description: Result of a shape query in Physics2DServer.

PinJoint2D.name: PinJoint2D
PinJoint2D.description: Pin Joint for 2D Rigid Bodies. It pins 2 bodies (rigid or static) together, or a single body to a fixed position in space.

Plane.name: Plane
Plane.description: Plane represents a normalized plane equation. Basically, "normal" is the normal of the plane (a,b,c normalized), and "d" is the distance from the origin to the plane (in the direction of "normal"). "Over" or "Above" the plane is considered the side of the plane towards where the normal is pointing.

methods.name: Plane
methods.description: Creates a plane from the three parameters "a", "b", "c" and "d".

methods.name: Plane
methods.description: Creates a plane from three points.

methods.name: Plane
methods.description: Creates a plane from the normal and the plane's distance to the origin.

methods.name: center
methods.description: Returns the center of the plane.

methods.name: distance_to
methods.description: Returns the shortest distance from the plane to the position "point".

methods.name: get_any_point
methods.description: Returns a point on the plane.

methods.name: has_point
methods.description: Returns true if "point" is inside the plane (by a very minimum threshold).

methods.name: intersect_3
methods.description: Returns the intersection point of the three planes "b", "c" and this plane. If no intersection is found null is returned.

methods.name: intersects_ray
methods.description: Returns the intersection point of a ray consisting of the position "from" and the direction normal "dir" with this plane. If no intersection is found null is returned.

methods.name: intersects_segment
methods.description: Returns the intersection point of a segment from position "begin" to position "end" with this plane. If no intersection is found null is returned.

methods.name: is_point_over
methods.description: Returns true if "point" is located above the plane.

methods.name: normalized
methods.description: Returns a copy of the plane, normalized.

methods.name: project
methods.description: Returns the orthogonal projection of point "p" into a point in the plane.

Polygon2D.name: Polygon2D
Polygon2D.description: A Polygon2D is defined by a set of n vertices connected together by line segments, meaning that the vertex 1 will be connected with vertex 2, vertex 2 with vertex 3 ..., vertex n-1 with vertex n and vertex n with vertex 1 in order to close the loop and define a polygon.

methods.name: get_color
methods.description: Return the polygon fill color.

methods.name: get_invert
methods.description: Return whether this polygon is inverted or not.

methods.name: get_invert_border
methods.description: Return the added padding around the bounding box.

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return the offset for the polygon vertices.

methods.name: get_polygon
methods.description: Return the set of vertices that defines this polygon.

methods.name: get_texture
methods.description: Return the polygon texture

methods.name: get_texture_offset
methods.description: Return the polygon texture offset.

methods.name: get_texture_rotation
methods.description: Return the rotation in radians of the texture polygon.

methods.name: get_texture_scale
methods.description: Return the uv coordinate multiplier.

methods.name: get_uv
methods.description: Return the texture coordinates associated with every vertex of the polygon.

methods.name: get_vertex_colors
methods.description: Return the list of vertex colors.

methods.name: set_color
methods.description: Set the polygon fill color. If the polygon has a texture defined, the defined texture will be multiplied by the polygon fill color. This, also, is the default color for those vertices that are not defined by [method get_vertex_colors].

methods.name: set_invert
methods.description: Set the polygon as the defined polygon bounding box minus the defined polygon (the defined polygon will appear as a hole on the square that contains the defined polygon).

methods.name: set_invert_border
methods.description: Add extra padding around the bounding box, making it bigger. Too small a value can make the polygon triangulate strangely, due to numerical imprecision.

methods.name: set_offset
methods.description: Set the an offset that will be added to the vertices' position. E.g. if the offset is set to (10,10) then all the polygon points will move 10 units to the right and 10 units to the bottom.

methods.name: set_polygon
methods.description: Define the set of vertices that will represent the polygon.

methods.name: set_texture
methods.description: Set the polygon texture.

methods.name: set_texture_offset
methods.description: Set the offset of the polygon texture. Initially the texture will appear anchored to the polygon position, the offset is used to move the texture location away from that point (notice that the texture origin is set to its top left corner, so when offset is 0,0 the top left corner of the texture is at the polygon position), for example setting the offset to 10, 10 will move the texture 10 units to the left and 10 units to the top.

methods.name: set_texture_rotation
methods.description: Set the amount of rotation of the polygon texture, [code]texture_rotation[/code] is specified in radians and clockwise rotation.

methods.name: set_texture_scale
methods.description: Set the value that will multiply the uv coordinates ([method get_uv]) when applying the texture. Larger values make the texture smaller, and vice versa.

methods.name: set_uv
methods.description: Set the texture coordinates for every vertex of the polygon. There should be one uv vertex for every vertex in the polygon. If there are less, the undefined ones will be assumed to be (0,0). Extra uv vertices are ignored.

methods.name: set_vertex_colors
methods.description:
Set the color for each vertex of the polygon. There should be one color for every vertex in the polygon. If there are less, the undefined ones will be assumed to be [method get_color]. Extra color entries are ignored.
	Colors are interpolated between vertices, resulting in smooth gradients when they differ.

PoolByteArray.name: PoolByteArray
PoolByteArray.description: Raw byte array. Contains bytes. Optimized for memory usage, can't fragment the memory.

methods.name: PoolByteArray
methods.description: Create from a generic array.

methods.name: append_array
methods.description: Append an [PoolByteArray] at the end of this array.

methods.name: compress
methods.description: Returns a new [PoolByteArray] with the data compressed. The compression mode can be set using one of the COMPRESS_* constants of [File].

methods.name: decompress
methods.description: Returns a new [PoolByteArray] with the data decompressed. The buffer_size should be set as the size of the uncompressed data. The compression mode can be set using one of the COMPRESS_* constants of [File].

methods.name: get_string_from_ascii
methods.description: Returns a copy of the array's contents formatted as String. Fast alternative to get_string_from_utf8(), assuming the content is ASCII-only (unlike the UTF-8 function, this function maps every byte to a character in the string, so any multibyte sequence will be torn apart).

methods.name: get_string_from_utf8
methods.description: Returns a copy of the array's contents formatted as String, assuming the array is formatted as UTF-8. Slower than get_string_from_ascii(), but works for UTF-8. Usually you should prefer this function over get_string_from_ascii() to support international input.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last).

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Set the size of the [PoolByteArray]. If larger than the current size it will reserve some space beforehand, and if it is smaller it will cut off the array.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Change the byte at the given index.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the array.

methods.name: subarray
methods.description: Returns the slice of the [PoolByteArray] between indices (inclusive) as a new [PoolByteArray].  Any negative index is considered to be from the end of the array.

PoolColorArray.name: PoolColorArray
PoolColorArray.description: Array of Color, can only contains colors. Optimized for memory usage, can't fragment the memory.

methods.name: PoolColorArray
methods.description: Create from a generic array.

Popup.name: Popup
Popup.brief_description: Base container control for popups and dialogs.
Popup.description: Popup is a base [Control] used to show dialogs and popups. It's a subwindow and modal by default (see [Control]) and has helpers for custom popup behavior.

methods.name: is_exclusive
methods.description: Returns whether the popup will hide other popups when shown on the screen.

methods.name: popup
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form).

methods.name: popup_centered
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form) in the center of the screen, at the current size, or at a size determined by "size".

methods.name: popup_centered_minsize
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form) in the center of the screen, ensuring the size is never smaller than [code]minsize[/code].

methods.name: popup_centered_ratio
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form) in the center of the screen, scaled at a ratio of size of the screen.

methods.name: set_exclusive
methods.description: Make the popup hide other popups when shown on the screen.

signals.name: about_to_show
signals.description: This signal is emitted when a popup is about to be shown. (often used in [PopupMenu] for clearing the list of options and creating a new one according to the current context).

signals.name: popup_hide
signals.description: This signal is emitted when a popup is hidden.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_POST_POPUP
constants.description: Notification sent right after the popup is shown.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_POPUP_HIDE
constants.description: Notification sent right after the popup is hidden.

PopupDialog.name: PopupDialog
PopupDialog.description: PopupDialog is a base class for popup dialogs, along with [WindowDialog].

PopupMenu.name: PopupMenu
PopupMenu.brief_description: PopupMenu displays a list of options.
PopupMenu.description: PopupMenu is the typical Control that displays a list of options. They are popular in toolbars or context menus.

methods.name: add_check_item
methods.description: Add a new checkable item with text "label". An id can optionally be provided, as well as an accelerator. If no id is provided, one will be created from the index. Note that checkable items just display a checkmark, but don't have any built-in checking behavior and must be checked/unchecked manually.

methods.name: add_icon_check_item
methods.description: Add a new checkable item with text "label" and icon "texture". An id can optionally be provided, as well as an accelerator. If no id is provided, one will be created from the index. Note that checkable items just display a checkmark, but don't have any built-in checking behavior and must be checked/unchecked manually.

methods.name: add_icon_item
methods.description: Add a new item with text "label" and icon "texture". An id can optionally be provided, as well as an accelerator keybinding. If no id is provided, one will be created from the index.

methods.name: add_item
methods.description: Add a new item with text "label". An id can optionally be provided, as well as an accelerator keybinding. If no id is provided, one will be created from the index.

methods.name: add_separator
methods.description: Add a separator between items. Separators also occupy an index.

methods.name: add_submenu_item
methods.description: Adds an item with a submenu. The submenu is the name of a child PopupMenu node that would be shown when the item is clicked. An id can optionally be provided, but if is isn't provided, one will be created from the index.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the popup menu, in effect removing all items.

methods.name: get_item_ID
methods.description: Return the id of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_item_accelerator
methods.description: Return the accelerator of the item at index "idx". Accelerators are special combinations of keys that activate the item, no matter which control is focused.

methods.name: get_item_count
methods.description: Return the amount of items.

methods.name: get_item_icon
methods.description: Return the icon of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_item_index
methods.description: Find and return the index of the item containing a given id.

methods.name: get_item_metadata
methods.description: Return the metadata of an item, which might be of any type. You can set it with [method set_item_metadata], which provides a simple way of assigning context data to items.

methods.name: get_item_submenu
methods.description: Return the submenu name of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_item_text
methods.description: Return the text of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: is_hide_on_checkable_item_selection
methods.description: Returns a boolean that indicates whether or not the PopupMenu will hide on checkable item selection.

methods.name: is_hide_on_item_selection
methods.description: Returns a boolean that indicates whether or not the PopupMenu will hide on item selection.

methods.name: is_item_checkable
methods.description: Return whether the item at index "idx" has a checkbox. Note that checkable items just display a checkmark, but don't have any built-in checking behavior and must be checked/unchecked manually.

methods.name: is_item_checked
methods.description: Return the checkstate status of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: is_item_disabled
methods.description: Return whether the item at index "idx" is disabled. When it is disabled it can't be selected, or its action invoked.

methods.name: is_item_separator
methods.description: Return whether the item is a seperator. If it is, it would be displayed as a line.

methods.name: remove_item
methods.description: Removes the item at index "idx" from the menu. Note that the indexes of items after the removed item are going to be shifted by one.

methods.name: set_hide_on_checkable_item_selection
methods.description: Sets whether or not the PopupMenu will hide on checkable item selection.

methods.name: set_hide_on_item_selection
methods.description: Sets whether or not the PopupMenu will hide on item selection.

methods.name: set_item_ID
methods.description: Set the id of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: set_item_accelerator
methods.description: Set the accelerator of the item at index "idx". Accelerators are special combinations of keys that activate the item, no matter which control is focused.

methods.name: set_item_as_checkable
methods.description: Set whether the item at index "idx" has a checkbox. Note that checkable items just display a checkmark, but don't have any built-in checking behavior and must be checked/unchecked manually.

methods.name: set_item_as_separator
methods.description: Mark the item at index "idx" as a seperator, which means that it would be displayed as a mere line.

methods.name: set_item_checked
methods.description: Set the checkstate status of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: set_item_disabled
methods.description: Sets whether the item at index "idx" is disabled or not. When it is disabled it can't be selected, or its action invoked.

methods.name: set_item_icon
methods.description: Set the icon of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: set_item_metadata
methods.description: Sets the metadata of an item, which might be of any type. You can later get it with [method get_item_metadata], which provides a simple way of assigning context data to items.

methods.name: set_item_submenu
methods.description: Sets the submenu of the item at index "idx". The submenu is the name of a child PopupMenu node that would be shown when the item is clicked.

methods.name: set_item_text
methods.description: Set the text of the item at index "idx".

signals.name: id_pressed
signals.description: This event is emitted when an item of some id is pressed or its accelerator is activated.

signals.name: index_pressed
signals.description: This event is emitted when an item of some index is pressed or its accelerator is activated.

PopupPanel.name: PopupPanel
PopupPanel.brief_description: Class for displaying popups with a panel background.
PopupPanel.description: Class for displaying popups with a panel background. In some cases it might be simpler to use than [Popup], since it provides a configurable background. If you are making windows, better check [WindowDialog].

Portal.name: Portal
Portal.brief_description: Portals provide virtual openings to rooms.
Portal.description: Portals provide virtual openings to [VisualInstance] nodes, so cameras can look at them from the outside. Note that portals are a visibility optimization technique, and are in no way related to the game of the same name (as in, they are not used for teleportation). For more information on how rooms and portals work, see [VisualInstance]. Portals are represented as 2D convex polygon shapes (in the X,Y local plane), and are placed on the surface of the areas occupied by a [VisualInstance], to indicate that the room can be accessed or looked-at through them. If two rooms are next to each other, and two similar portals in each of them share the same world position (and are parallel and opposed to each other), they will automatically "connect" and form "doors" (for example, the portals that connect a kitchen to a living room are placed in the door they share). Portals must always have a [VisualInstance] node as a parent, grandparent or far parent, or else they will not be active.

methods.name: get_connect_range
methods.description: Return the range for auto-connecting two portals from different rooms sharing the same space.

methods.name: get_disable_distance
methods.description: Return the distance threshold for disabling the portal. Every time that the portal goes beyond "distance", it disables itself, becoming the opaque color (see [method set_disabled_color]).

methods.name: get_disabled_color
methods.description: Return the color for when the portal goes beyond the disable distance (see [method set_disable_distance]) and becomes disabled.

methods.name: get_shape
methods.description: Return the portal shape. The shape is an array of [Vector2] points, representing a convex polygon in the X,Y plane.

methods.name: is_enabled
methods.description: Return whether the portal is active. When disabled it causes the parent [VisualInstance] to not be visible any longer when looking through the portal.

methods.name: set_connect_range
methods.description: Set the range for auto-connecting two portals from different rooms sharing the same space.

methods.name: set_disable_distance
methods.description: Set the distance threshold for disabling the portal. Every time that the portal goes beyond "distance", it disables itself, becoming the opaque color (see [method set_disabled_color]).

methods.name: set_disabled_color
methods.description: When the portal goes beyond the disable distance (see [method set_disable_distance]), it becomes opaque and displayed with color "color".

methods.name: set_enabled
methods.description: Enable the portal (it is enabled by default though), disabling it will cause the parent [VisualInstance] to not be visible any longer when looking through the portal.

methods.name: set_shape
methods.description: Set the portal shape. The shape is an array of [Vector2] points, representing a convex polygon in the X,Y plane.

Position2D.name: Position2D
Position2D.description: Generic 2D Position hint for editing. It's just like a plain [Node2D] but displays as a cross in the 2D-Editor at all times.

Position3D.name: Position3D
Position3D.description: Generic 3D Position hint for editing. It's just like a plain [Spatial] but displays as a cross in the 3D-Editor at all times.

ProgressBar.name: ProgressBar
ProgressBar.description: General purpose progress bar. Shows fill percentage from right to left.

Quat.name: Quat
Quat.description: Quaternion is a 4 dimensional vector that is used to represent a rotation. It mainly exists to perform SLERP (spherical-linear interpolation) between two rotations. Multiplying quaternions also cheaply reproduces rotation sequences. However quaternions need to be often renormalized, or else they suffer from precision issues.

methods.name: Quat
methods.description: Returns a quaternion that will rotate around the given axis by the specified angle. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: Quat
methods.description: Returns the rotation matrix corresponding to the given quaternion.

methods.name: dot
methods.description: Returns the dot product of two quaternions.

methods.name: inverse
methods.description: Returns the inverse of the quaternion.

methods.name: is_normalized
methods.description: Returns whether the quaternion is normalized or not.

methods.name: length
methods.description: Returns the length of the quaternion.

methods.name: length_squared
methods.description: Returns the length of the quaternion, squared.

methods.name: normalized
methods.description: Returns a copy of the quaternion, normalized to unit length.

methods.name: slerp
methods.description: Perform a spherical-linear interpolation with another quaternion.

RID.name: RID
RID.description: The RID type is used to access the unique integer ID of a resource.  They are opaque, so they do not grant access to the associated resource by themselves. They are used by and with the low-level Server classes such as [VisualServer].

methods.name: RID
methods.description: Create a new RID instance with the ID of a given resource. When not handed a valid resource, silently stores the unused ID 0.

methods.name: get_id
methods.description: Retrieve the ID of the referenced resource.

Range.name: Range
Range.brief_description: Abstract base class for range-based controls.
Range.description: Range is a base class for [Control] nodes that change a floating point [i]value[/i] between a [i]minimum[/i] and a [i]maximum[/i], using [i]step[/i] and [i]page[/i], for example a [ScrollBar].

methods.name: get_as_ratio
methods.description: Return value mapped to 0 to 1 range.

methods.name: get_max
methods.description: Return the maximum value.

methods.name: get_min
methods.description: Return the minimum value.

methods.name: get_page
methods.description: Return the page size, if page is 0, paging is disabled.

methods.name: get_step
methods.description: Return the stepping, if step is 0, stepping is disabled.

methods.name: set_as_ratio
methods.description: Set value mapped to 0 to 1 (unit) range, it will then be converted to the actual value within min and max.

methods.name: set_min
methods.description: Set minimum value, clamped range value to it if it's less.

methods.name: set_page
methods.description: Set page size. Page is mainly used for scrollbars or anything that controls text scrolling.

methods.name: set_step
methods.description: Set step value. If step is 0, stepping will be disabled.

signals.name: changed
signals.description: This signal is emitted when min, max, range or step change.

signals.name: value_changed
signals.description: This signal is emitted when value changes.

RayCast.name: RayCast
RayCast.brief_description: Query the closest object intersecting a ray.
RayCast.description:
A RayCast represents a line from its origin to its destination position [code]cast_to[/code], it is used to query the 3D space in order to find the closest object intersecting with the ray.

		RayCast can ignore some objects by adding them to the exception list via [code]add_exception[/code], setting proper filtering with layers, or by filtering object types with type masks.

		Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions!

		RayCast calculates intersection every fixed frame (see [Node]), and the result is cached so it can be used later until the next frame. If multiple queries are required between fixed frames (or during the same frame) use [method force_raycast_update] after adjusting the raycast.

methods.name: add_exception
methods.description: Adds a collision exception so the ray does not report collisions with the specified [code]node[/code].

methods.name: clear_exceptions
methods.description: Removes all collision exception for this ray.

methods.name: force_raycast_update
methods.description: Updates the collision information in case if this object's properties changed during the current frame (for example position, rotation or the cast_point). Note, [code]set_enabled[/code] is not required for this to work.

methods.name: get_cast_to
methods.description: Return the destination point of this ray object.

methods.name: get_collider
methods.description: Return the closest object the ray is pointing to. Note that this does not consider the length of the vector, so you must also use [method is_colliding] to check if the object returned is actually colliding with the ray.

methods.name: get_collider_shape
methods.description: Returns the collision shape of the closest object the ray is pointing to.

methods.name: get_collision_layer
methods.description: Returns the collision layer for this ray.

methods.name: get_collision_normal
methods.description: Returns the normal of the intersecting object shape face containing the collision point.

methods.name: get_collision_point
methods.description: Returns collision point. This point is in [b]global[/b] coordinate system.

methods.name: get_type_mask
methods.description: Returns the type mask (types of objects to detect) for this ray. The value is a sum (bitwise OR'd) of constants available for [PhysicsDirectSpaceState].

methods.name: is_colliding
methods.description: Return whether the closest object the ray is pointing to is colliding with the vector (considering the vector length).

methods.name: is_enabled
methods.description: Returns whether this raycast is enabled or not.

methods.name: remove_exception
methods.description: Removes a collision exception so the ray does report collisions with the specified [code]node[/code].

methods.name: set_cast_to
methods.description: Sets to which point ray should be casted. This point is in [b]local[/b] coordinate system.

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description: Set the mask to filter objects. Only objects with at least the same mask element set will be detected.

methods.name: set_enabled
methods.description: Enables the RayCast2D. Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions.

methods.name: set_type_mask
methods.description: Set the types of objects to detect. For [code]mask[/code] use a logic sum (OR operation) of constants defined in [PhysicsDirectSpaceState], eg. [code]PhysicsDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_STATIC_BODY | PhysicsDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_KINEMATIC_BODY[/code] to detect only those two types.

RayCast2D.name: RayCast2D
RayCast2D.brief_description: Query the closest object intersecting a ray.
RayCast2D.description:
A RayCast2D represents a line from its origin to its destination position [code]cast_to[/code], it is used to query the 2D space in order to find the closest object intersecting with the ray.

		RayCast2D can ignore some objects by adding them to the exception list via [code]add_exception[/code], setting proper filtering with layers, or by filtering object types with type masks.

		Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions!

		RayCast2D calculates intersection every fixed frame (see [Node]), and the result is cached so it can be used later until the next frame. If multiple queries are required between fixed frames (or during the same frame) use [method force_raycast_update] after adjusting the raycast.

methods.name: add_exception
methods.description: Adds a collision exception so the ray does not report collisions with the specified [code]node[/code].

methods.name: clear_exceptions
methods.description: Removes all collision exception for this ray.

methods.name: force_raycast_update
methods.description: Updates the collision information in case if this object's properties changed during the current frame (for example position, rotation or the cast_point). Note, [code]set_enabled[/code] is not required for this to work.

methods.name: get_cast_to
methods.description: Return the destination point of this ray object.

methods.name: get_collider
methods.description: Return the closest object the ray is pointing to. Note that this does not consider the length of the vector, so you must also use [method is_colliding] to check if the object returned is actually colliding with the ray.

methods.name: get_collider_shape
methods.description: Returns the collision shape of the closest object the ray is pointing to.

methods.name: get_collision_layer
methods.description: Returns the collision layer for this ray.

methods.name: get_collision_normal
methods.description: Returns the normal of the intersecting object shape face containing the collision point.

methods.name: get_collision_point
methods.description: Returns the collision point in which the ray intersects the closest object. This point is in [b]global[/b] coordinate system.

methods.name: get_exclude_parent_body
methods.description: Returns whether this ray should hit your parent node, if it's a body.

methods.name: get_type_mask
methods.description: Returns the type mask (types of objects to detect) for this ray. The value is a sum (bitwise OR'd) of constants available for [Physics2DDirectSpaceState].

methods.name: is_colliding
methods.description: Return whether the closest object the ray is pointing to is colliding with the vector (considering the vector length).

methods.name: is_enabled
methods.description: Returns whether this raycast is enabled or not.

methods.name: remove_exception
methods.description: Removes a collision exception so the ray does report collisions with the specified [code]node[/code].

methods.name: set_cast_to
methods.description: Sets the ray destination point, so that the ray will test from the ray's origin to [code]local_point[/code]

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description: Set the mask to filter objects. Only objects with at least the same mask element set will be detected.

methods.name: set_enabled
methods.description: Enables the RayCast2D. Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions.

methods.name: set_exclude_parent_body
methods.description: Toggle whether this ray should hit your parent node, if it's a body.

methods.name: set_type_mask
methods.description: Set the types of objects to detect. For [code]mask[/code] use a logic sum (OR operation) of constants defined in [Physics2DDirectSpaceState], eg. [code]Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_STATIC_BODY | Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_KINEMATIC_BODY[/code] to detect only those two types.

RayShape2D.name: RayShape2D
RayShape2D.description: Ray 2D shape resource for physics. A ray is not really a collision body, instead it tries to separate itself from whatever is touching its far endpoint. It's often useful for characters.

methods.name: get_length
methods.description: Return the length of the ray.

methods.name: set_length
methods.description: Set the length of the ray.

Rect2.name: Rect2
Rect2.description: Rect2 provides an 2D Axis-Aligned Bounding Box. It consists of a position, a size, and several utility functions. It is typically used for fast overlap tests.

methods.name: Rect2
methods.description: Construct a [Rect2] by position and size.

methods.name: Rect2
methods.description: Construct a [Rect2] by x, y, width and height.

methods.name: clip
methods.description: Returns the intersection of this [Rect2] and b.

methods.name: encloses
methods.description: Returns true if this [Rect2] completely encloses another one.

methods.name: expand
methods.description: Return this [Rect2] expanded to include a given point.

methods.name: get_area
methods.description: Get the area of the [Rect2].

methods.name: grow
methods.description: Return a copy of the [Rect2] grown a given amount of units towards all the sides.

methods.name: has_no_area
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect2] is flat or empty.

methods.name: has_point
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect2] contains a point.

methods.name: intersects
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect2] overlaps with another.

methods.name: merge
methods.description: Combine this [Rect2] with another, a larger one is returned that contains both.

Rect3.name: Rect3
Rect3.description: Rect3 provides an 3D Axis-Aligned Bounding Box. It consists of a position, a size, and several utility functions. It is typically used for simple (fast) overlap tests.

methods.name: Rect3
methods.description: Optional constructor, accepts position and size.

methods.name: encloses
methods.description: Return true if this [Rect3] completely encloses another one.

methods.name: expand
methods.description: Return this [Rect3] expanded to include a given point.

methods.name: get_area
methods.description: Get the area of the [Rect3].

methods.name: get_endpoint
methods.description: Get the position of the 8 endpoints of the [Rect3] in space.

methods.name: get_longest_axis
methods.description: Return the normalized longest axis of the [Rect3].

methods.name: get_longest_axis_index
methods.description: Return the index of the longest axis of the [Rect3] (according to [Vector3]::AXIS* enum).

methods.name: get_longest_axis_size
methods.description: Return the scalar length of the longest axis of the [Rect3].

methods.name: get_shortest_axis
methods.description: Return the normalized shortest axis of the [Rect3].

methods.name: get_shortest_axis_index
methods.description: Return the index of the shortest axis of the [Rect3] (according to [Vector3]::AXIS* enum).

methods.name: get_shortest_axis_size
methods.description: Return the scalar length of the shortest axis of the [Rect3].

methods.name: get_support
methods.description: Return the support point in a given direction. This is useful for collision detection algorithms.

methods.name: grow
methods.description: Return a copy of the [Rect3] grown a given amount of units towards all the sides.

methods.name: has_no_area
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect3] is flat or empty.

methods.name: has_no_surface
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect3] is empty.

methods.name: has_point
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect3] contains a point.

methods.name: intersection
methods.description: Return the intersection between two [Rect3]. An empty Rect3 (size 0,0,0) is returned on failure.

methods.name: intersects
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect3] overlaps with another.

methods.name: intersects_plane
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect3] is at both sides of a plane.

methods.name: intersects_segment
methods.description: Return true if the [Rect3] intersects the line segment between from and to

methods.name: merge
methods.description: Combine this [Rect3] with another, a larger one is returned that contains both.

RectangleShape2D.name: RectangleShape2D
RectangleShape2D.description: Rectangle Shape for 2D Physics. This shape is useful for modeling box-like 2D objects.

methods.name: get_extents
methods.description: Return the half extents, the actual width and height of this shape is twice the half extents.

methods.name: set_extents
methods.description: Set the half extents, the actual width and height of this shape is twice the half extents.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.brief_description: Base class for anything that keeps a reference count.
Reference.description: Base class for anything that keeps a reference count. Resource and many other helper objects inherit this. References keep an internal reference counter so they are only released when no longer in use.

methods.name: reference
methods.description: Increase the internal reference counter. Use this only if you really know what you are doing.

methods.name: unreference
methods.description: Decrease the internal reference counter. Use this only if you really know what you are doing.

ReferenceRect.name: ReferenceRect
ReferenceRect.description: Reference frame for GUI. It's just like an empty control, except a red box is displayed while editing around its size at all times.

RegEx.name: RegEx
RegEx.description:
Class for finding text patterns in a string using regular expressions. It can not perform replacements. Regular expressions are a way to define patterns of text to be searched. Details on writing patterns are too long to explain here but the Internet is full of tutorials and detailed explanations.
		Once created, the RegEx object needs to be compiled with the pattern before it can be used. The pattern must be escaped first for gdscript before it is escaped for the expression. For example:
		[code]var exp = RegEx.new()[/code]
		[code]exp.compile("\\d+")[/code]
		would be read by RegEx as [code]\d+[/code]
		Similarly:
		[code]exp.compile("\"(?:\\\\.|[^\"])*\"")[/code]
		would be read as [code]"(?:\\.|[^"])*"[/code]
		Currently supported features:
		* Capturing [code]()[/code] and non-capturing [code](?:)[/code] groups
		* Named capturing groups [code](?P<name>)[/code]
		* Any character [code].[/code]
		* Shorthand character classes [code]\w \W \s \S \d \D[/code]
		* User-defined character classes such as [code][A-Za-z][/code]
		* Simple quantifiers [code]?[/code], [code]*[/code] and [code]+[/code]
		* Range quantifiers [code]{x,y}[/code]
		* Lazy (non-greedy) quantifiers [code]*?[/code]
		* Beginning [code]^[/code] and end [code]$[/code] anchors
		* Alternation [code]|[/code]
		* Backreferences [code]\1[/code], [code]\g{1}[/code], and [code]\g<name>[/code]
		* POSIX character classes [code][[:alnum:]][/code]
		* Lookahead [code](?=)[/code], [code](?!)[/code] and lookbehind [code](?<=)[/code], [code](?<!)[/code]
		* ASCII [code]\xFF[/code] and Unicode [code]\uFFFF[/code] code points (in a style similar to Python)
		* Word boundaries [code]\b[/code], [code]\B[/code]

methods.name: clear
methods.description: This method resets the state of the object, as it was freshly created. Namely, it unassigns the regular expression of this object.

methods.name: compile
methods.description: Compiles and assign the regular expression pattern to use.

methods.name: get_group_count
methods.description: Returns the number of numeric capturing groups.

methods.name: get_names
methods.description: Returns an array of names of named capturing groups.

methods.name: get_pattern
methods.description: Returns the expression used to compile the code.

methods.name: is_valid
methods.description: Returns whether this object has a valid regular expression assigned.

methods.name: search
methods.description: Searches the text for the compiled pattern. Returns a [RegExMatch] container of the first matching reult if found, otherwise null. The region to search within can be specified without modifying where the start and end anchor would be.

methods.name: sub
methods.description: Searches the text for the compiled pattern and replaces it with the specified string. Escapes and backreferences such as [code]\1[/code] and [code]\g<name>[/code] expanded and resolved. By default only the first instance is replaced but it can be changed for all instances (global replacement). The region to search within can be specified without modifying where the start and end anchor would be.

methods.name: expand
methods.description: Using results from the search, returns the specified string with escapes and backreferences such as [code]\1[/code] and [code]\g<name>[/code] expanded and resolved.

methods.name: get_end
methods.description: Returns the end position of the match in the string. An integer can be specified for numeric groups or a string for named groups. Returns -1 if that group wasn't found or doesn't exist. Defaults to 0 (whole pattern).

methods.name: get_group_array
methods.description: Returns an array of the results of the numeric groups.

methods.name: get_group_count
methods.description: Returns the number of numeric capturing groups.

methods.name: get_name_dict
methods.description: Returns a dictionary containing the named capturing groups and their results.

methods.name: get_names
methods.description: Returns an array of names of named capturing groups.

methods.name: get_start
methods.description: Returns the starting position of the match in the string. An integer can be specified for numeric groups or a string for named groups. Returns -1 if that group wasn't found or doesn't exist. Defaults to 0 (whole pattern).

methods.name: get_string
methods.description: Returns the result of the match in the string. An integer can be specified for numeric groups or a string for named groups. Returns -1 if that group wasn't found or doesn't exist. Defaults to 0 (whole pattern).

Resource.name: Resource
Resource.description: Resource is the base class for all resource types. Resources are primarily data containers. They are reference counted and freed when no longer in use. They are also loaded only once from disk, and further attempts to load the resource will return the same reference (all this in contrast to a [Node], which is not reference counted and can be instanced from disk as many times as desired). Resources can be saved externally on disk or bundled into another object, such as a [Node] or another resource.

methods.name: get_name
methods.description: Return the name of the resources, any name is valid (it doesn't have to be unique). Name is for descriptive purposes only.

methods.name: get_path
methods.description: Return the path of the resource. This is useful mainly for editors when saving/loading, and shouldn't be changed by anything else.

methods.name: get_rid
methods.description: Return the RID of the resource (or an empty RID). Many resources (such as [Texture], [Mesh], etc) are high level abstractions of resources stored in a server, so this function will return the original RID.

methods.name: set_name
methods.description: Set the name of the resources, any name is valid (it doesn't have to be unique). Name is for descriptive purposes only.

methods.name: set_path
methods.description: Set the path of the resource. This is useful mainly for editors when saving/loading, and shouldn't be changed by anything else. Fails if another [Resource] already has path "path".

methods.name: take_over_path
methods.description: Set the path of the resource. Differs from set_path(), if another [Resource] exists with "path" it over-takes it, instead of failing.

ResourceInteractiveLoader.name: ResourceInteractiveLoader
ResourceInteractiveLoader.description: Interactive Resource Loader. This object is returned by ResourceLoader when performing an interactive load. It allows to load with high granularity, so this is mainly useful for displaying load bars/percentages.

methods.name: get_resource
methods.description: Return the loaded resource (only if loaded). Otherwise, returns null.

methods.name: get_stage
methods.description: Return the load stage. The total amount of stages can be queried with [method get_stage_count]

methods.name: get_stage_count
methods.description: Return the total amount of stages (calls to [method poll]) needed to completely load this resource.

methods.name: poll
methods.description: Poll the load. If OK is returned, this means poll will have to be called again. If ERR_FILE_EOF is returned, them the load has finished and the resource can be obtained by calling [method get_resource].

ResourceLoader.name: ResourceLoader
ResourceLoader.description: Resource Loader. This is a static object accessible as [ResourceLoader]. GDScript has a simplified load() function, though.

methods.name: get_recognized_extensions_for_type
methods.description: Return the list of recognized extensions for a resource type.

methods.name: load_interactive
methods.description: Load a resource interactively, the returned object allows to load with high granularity.

methods.name: set_abort_on_missing_resources
methods.description: Change the behavior on missing sub-resources. Default is to abort load.

ResourcePreloader.name: ResourcePreloader
ResourcePreloader.description: Resource Preloader Node. This node is used to preload sub-resources inside a scene, so when the scene is loaded all the resources are ready to use and be retrieved from here.

methods.name: add_resource
methods.description: Add a resource to the preloader. Set the text-id that will be used to identify it (retrieve it/erase it/etc).

methods.name: get_resource
methods.description: Return the resource given a text-id.

methods.name: get_resource_list
methods.description: Return the list of resources inside the preloader.

methods.name: has_resource
methods.description: Return true if the preloader has a given resource.

methods.name: remove_resource
methods.description: Remove a resource from the preloader by text id.

methods.name: rename_resource
methods.description: Rename a resource inside the preloader, from a text-id to a new text-id.

ResourceSaver.name: ResourceSaver
ResourceSaver.description: Resource Saving Interface. This interface is used for saving resources to disk.

methods.name: get_recognized_extensions
methods.description: Return the list of extensions available for saving a resource of a given type.

methods.name: save
methods.description: Save a resource to disk, to a given path.

RichTextLabel.name: RichTextLabel
RichTextLabel.description: Label that displays rich text. Rich text can contain custom text, fonts, images and some basic formatting. It also adapts itself to given width/heights.

methods.name: get_text
methods.description: Returns the raw text, stripping out the formatting information.

methods.name: is_selection_enabled
methods.description: Return true if selecting the text inside this richtext is allowed.

methods.name: set_selection_enabled
methods.description: Set to true if selecting the text inside this richtext is allowed.

RigidBody.name: RigidBody
RigidBody.description: Rigid body node. This node is used for placing rigid bodies in the scene. It can contain a number of shapes, and also shift mode between regular Rigid body, Kinematic, Character or Static.
