methods.name: _integrate_forces
methods.description: Called during physics processing, allowing you to read and safely modify the simulation state for the object. By default it works in addition to the usual physics behavior, but [method set_use_custom_integrator] allows you to disable the default behavior and do fully custom force integration for a body.

methods.name: apply_impulse
methods.description: Apply a positioned impulse (which will be affected by the body mass and shape). This is the equivalent of hitting a billiard ball with a cue: a force that is applied once, and only once. Both the impulse and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: get_angular_damp
methods.description: Return the current body angular damp. Default is -1.

methods.name: get_angular_velocity
methods.description: Return the current body angular velocity.

methods.name: get_axis_lock
methods.description: Return the current axis lock of the body. One of AXIS_LOCK_* enum.

methods.name: get_bounce
methods.description: Return the current body bounciness.

methods.name: get_colliding_bodies
methods.description: Return a list of the bodies colliding with this one. By default, number of max contacts reported is at 0 , see [method set_max_contacts_reported] to increase it.

methods.name: get_friction
methods.description: Return the current body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction).

methods.name: get_gravity_scale
methods.description: Return the current body gravity scale.

methods.name: get_linear_damp
methods.description: Return the current body linear damp. Default is -1.

methods.name: get_linear_velocity
methods.description: Return the current body linear velocity.

methods.name: get_mass
methods.description: Return the current body mass.

methods.name: get_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Return the maximum contacts that can be reported. See [method set_max_contacts_reported].

methods.name: get_mode
methods.description: Return the current body mode, see [method set_mode].

methods.name: get_weight
methods.description: Return the current body weight, given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8).

methods.name: is_able_to_sleep
methods.description: Return whether the body has the ability to fall asleep when not moving. See [method set_can_sleep].

methods.name: is_contact_monitor_enabled
methods.description: Return whether contact monitoring is enabled.

methods.name: is_sleeping
methods.description: Return whether the body is sleeping.

methods.name: is_using_continuous_collision_detection
methods.description: Return whether this body is using continuous collision detection.

methods.name: is_using_custom_integrator
methods.description: Return whether the body is using a custom integrator.

methods.name: set_angular_damp
methods.description: Set the angular damp for this body. Default of -1, cannot be less than -1. If this value is different from -1, any angular damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_angular_velocity
methods.description: Set the body angular velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_axis_lock
methods.description: Set the axis lock of the body, from the AXIS_LOCK_* enum. Axis lock stops the body from moving along the specified axis(X/Y/Z) and rotating along the other two axes.

methods.name: set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Set an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: set_bounce
methods.description: Set the body bounciness, from 0 (no bounciness) to 1 (max bounciness).

methods.name: set_can_sleep
methods.description:
Set the body ability to fall asleep when not moving. This saves an enormous amount of processor time when there are plenty of rigid bodies (non static) in a scene.
				Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] / [method set_applied_force] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_contact_monitor
methods.description: Enable contact monitoring. This allows the body to emit signals when it collides with another.

methods.name: set_friction
methods.description: Set the body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction).

methods.name: set_gravity_scale
methods.description: Set the gravity factor. This factor multiplies gravity intensity just for this body.

methods.name: set_linear_damp
methods.description: Set the linear damp for this body. Default of -1, cannot be less than -1. If this value is different from -1, any linear damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_linear_velocity
methods.description: Set the body linear velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_mass
methods.description: Set the body mass.

methods.name: set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Set the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: set_mode
methods.description: Set the body mode, from the MODE_* enum. This allows to change to a static body or a character body.

methods.name: set_sleeping
methods.description: Set whether a body is sleeping or not. Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_use_continuous_collision_detection
methods.description:
Set the continuous collision detection mode from the enum CCD_MODE_*.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided. The first is more precise, and misses less impacts by small, fast-moving objects. The second is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

methods.name: set_use_custom_integrator
methods.description: Pass true to disable the internal force integration (like gravity or air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function, if defined.

methods.name: set_weight
methods.description: Set the body weight given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8).

signals.name: body_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_shape_entered
signals.description:
Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that collided with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body collided with.

signals.name: body_shape_exited
signals.description:
Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that stopped colliding with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body stopped colliding with.

signals.name: sleeping_state_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the body changes its sleeping state. Either by sleeping or waking up.

constants.name: MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Static mode. The body behaves like a [StaticBody], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Kinematic body. The body behaves like a [KinematicBody], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Rigid body. This is the "natural" state of a rigid body. It is affected by forces, and can move, rotate, and be affected by user code.

constants.name: MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Character body. This behaves like a rigid body, but can not rotate.

RigidBody2D.name: RigidBody2D
RigidBody2D.description:
Rigid body 2D node. This node is used for placing rigid bodies in the scene. It can contain a number of shapes, and also shift state between regular Rigid body, Kinematic, Character or Static.
		Character mode forbids the node from being rotated. This node can have a custom force integrator function, for writing complex physics motion behavior per node.
		As a warning, don't change this node position every frame or very often. Sporadic changes work fine, but physics runs at a different granularity (fixed hz) than usual rendering (process callback) and maybe even in a separate thread, so changing this from a process loop will yield strange behavior.

methods.name: _integrate_forces
methods.description: Called during physics processing, allowing you to read and safely modify the simulation state for the object. By default it works in addition to the usual physics behavior, but [method set_use_custom_integrator] allows you to disable the default behavior and do fully custom force integration for a body.

methods.name: add_force
methods.description: Add a positioned force to the applied force and torque. As with [method apply_impulse], both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: apply_impulse
methods.description: Apply a positioned impulse (which will be affected by the body mass and shape). This is the equivalent of hitting a billiard ball with a cue: a force that is applied once, and only once. Both the impulse and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: get_angular_damp
methods.description: Return the angular damp for this body.

methods.name: get_angular_velocity
methods.description: Return the body angular velocity. This changes by physics granularity. See [method set_angular_velocity].

methods.name: get_applied_force
methods.description: Return the applied force vector.

methods.name: get_applied_torque
methods.description: Return the torque which is being applied to this body.

methods.name: get_bounce
methods.description: Return the body bounciness.

methods.name: get_colliding_bodies
methods.description: Return a list of the bodies colliding with this one. By default, number of max contacts reported is at 0 , see [method set_max_contacts_reported] to increase it. You must also enable contact monitor, see [method set_contact_monitor]

methods.name: get_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description: Return whether this body is using continuous collision detection.

methods.name: get_friction
methods.description: Return the body friction.

methods.name: get_gravity_scale
methods.description: Return the gravity factor.

methods.name: get_inertia
methods.description: Return the body's moment of inertia. This is usually automatically computed from the mass and the shapes. Note that this doesn't seem to work in a [code]_ready[/code] function: it apparently has not been auto-computed yet.

methods.name: get_linear_damp
methods.description: Return the linear damp for this body.

methods.name: get_linear_velocity
methods.description: Return the body linear velocity. This changes by physics granularity. See [method set_linear_velocity].

methods.name: get_mass
methods.description: Return the body mass.

methods.name: get_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Return the maximum contacts that can be reported. See [method set_max_contacts_reported].

methods.name: get_mode
methods.description: Return the current body mode, see [method set_mode].

methods.name: get_weight
methods.description: Return the body weight given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8).

methods.name: is_able_to_sleep
methods.description: Return true if the body has the ability to fall asleep when not moving. See [method set_can_sleep].

methods.name: is_contact_monitor_enabled
methods.description: Return whether contact monitoring is enabled.

methods.name: is_sleeping
methods.description: Return whether the body is sleeping.

methods.name: is_using_custom_integrator
methods.description: Return true if the body is not doing any built-in force integration.

methods.name: set_angular_damp
methods.description: Set the angular damp for this body. If this value is different from -1, any angular damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_angular_velocity
methods.description: Set the body angular velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_applied_force
methods.description: Set the applied force vector. This is the equivalent of pushing a box over the ground: the force applied is applied constantly.

methods.name: set_applied_torque
methods.description: Set a constant torque which will be applied to this body.

methods.name: set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Set an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: set_bounce
methods.description: Set the body bounciness, from 0 (no bounce) to 1 (full bounce).

methods.name: set_can_sleep
methods.description:
Set the body ability to fall asleep when not moving. This saves an enormous amount of processor time when there are plenty of rigid bodies (non static) in a scene.
				Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] / [method set_applied_force] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_contact_monitor
methods.description: Enable contact monitoring. This allows the body to emit signals when it collides with another.

methods.name: set_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description:
Set the continuous collision detection mode from the enum CCD_MODE_*.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided. The first is more precise, and misses less impacts by small, fast-moving objects. The second is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

methods.name: set_friction
methods.description: Set the body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (full friction).

methods.name: set_gravity_scale
methods.description: Set the gravity factor. This factor multiplies gravity intensity just for this body.

methods.name: set_inertia
methods.description: Set the body's moment of inertia. This is like mass, but for rotation: it determines how much torque it takes to rotate the body. The moment of inertia is usually computed automatically from the mass and the shapes, but this function allows you to set a custom value. Set 0 (or negative) inertia to return to automatically computing it.

methods.name: set_linear_damp
methods.description: Set the linear damp for this body. If this value is different from -1, any linear damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_linear_velocity
methods.description: Set the body linear velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_mass
methods.description: Set the body mass.

methods.name: set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Set the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: set_mode
methods.description: Set the body mode, from the MODE_* enum. This allows to change to a static body or a character body.

methods.name: set_sleeping
methods.description: Set whether a body is sleeping or not. Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] / [method set_applied_force] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_use_custom_integrator
methods.description: Pass true to disable the internal force integration (like gravity or air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function, if defined.

methods.name: set_weight
methods.description: Set the body weight given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8). Not really useful for 2D since most measures for this node are in pixels.

methods.name: test_motion
methods.description: Return whether the body would collide, if it tried to move in the given vector. This method allows two extra parameters: A margin, which increases slightly the size of the shapes involved in the collision detection, and an object of type [Physics2DTestMotionResult], which will store additional information about the collision (should there be one).

signals.name: body_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a body exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_shape_entered
signals.description:
Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that collided with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body collided with.

signals.name: body_shape_exited
signals.description:
Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that stopped colliding with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body stopped colliding with.

signals.name: sleeping_state_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the body changes its sleeping state. Either by sleeping or waking up.

constants.name: MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Static mode. The body behaves like a [StaticBody2D], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Kinematic body. The body behaves like a [KinematicBody2D], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Rigid body. This is the "natural" state of a rigid body. It is affected by forces, and can move, rotate, and be affected by user code.

constants.name: MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Character body. This behaves like a rigid body, but can not rotate.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Disables continuous collision detection. This is the fastest way to detect body collisions, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_RAY
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by raycasting. It is faster than shapecasting, but less precise.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_SHAPE
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by shapecasting. It is the slowest CCD method, and the most precise.

Room.name: Room
Room.description: Room contains the data to define the bounds of a scene (using a BSP Tree). It is instanced by a [VisualInstance] node to create rooms. See that class documentation for more information about rooms.

methods.name: has_network_peer
methods.description: Returns true if there is a [NetworkedMultiplayerPeer] set (with [method SceneTree.set_network_peer]).

methods.name: is_network_server
methods.description: Returns true if this SceneTree's [NetworkedMultiplayerPeer] is in server mode (listening for connections).

methods.name: set_network_peer
methods.description: Set the peer object to handle the RPC system (effectively enabling networking). Depending on the peer itself, the SceneTree will become a network server (check with [method is_network_server()]) and will set root node's network mode to master (see NETWORK_MODE_* constants in [Node]), or it will become a regular peer with root node set to slave. All child nodes are set to inherit the network mode by default. Handling of networking-related events (connection, disconnection, new clients) is done by connecting to SceneTree's signals.

Script.name: Script
Script.description: Base class for scripts. Any script that is loaded becomes one of these resources, which can then create instances.

methods.name: can_instance
methods.description: Return true if this script can be instance (ie not a library).

methods.name: get_source_code
methods.description: Return the script source code (if available).

methods.name: has_source_code
methods.description: Return true if the script contains source code.

methods.name: instance_has
methods.description: Return true if a given object uses an instance of this script.

methods.name: set_source_code
methods.description: Set the script source code.

ScrollBar.name: ScrollBar
ScrollBar.description: Scrollbars are a [Range] based [Control], that display a draggable area (the size of the page). Horizontal ([HScrollBar]) and Vertical ([VScrollBar]) versions are available.

ScrollContainer.name: ScrollContainer
ScrollContainer.brief_description: A helper node for displaying scrollable elements (e.g. lists).
ScrollContainer.description: A ScrollContainer node with a [Control] child and scrollbar child ([HScrollbar], [VScrollBar], or both) will only draw the Control within the ScrollContainer area.  Scrollbars will automatically be drawn at the right (for vertical) or bottom (for horizontal) and will enable dragging to move the viewable Control (and its children) within the ScrollContainer.  Scrollbars will also automatically resize the grabber based on the minimum_size of the Control relative to the ScrollContainer.  Works great with a [Panel] control.  You can set EXPAND on children size flags, so they will upscale to ScrollContainer size if ScrollContainer size is bigger (scroll is invisible for chosen dimension).

methods.name: get_h_scroll
methods.description: Return current horizontal scroll value.

methods.name: get_v_scroll
methods.description: Return current vertical scroll value.

methods.name: is_h_scroll_enabled
methods.description: Return true if horizontal scroll is allowed.

methods.name: is_v_scroll_enabled
methods.description: Return true if vertical scroll is allowed.

methods.name: set_enable_h_scroll
methods.description: Set allows horizontal scroll.

methods.name: set_enable_v_scroll
methods.description: Set allows vertical scroll.

methods.name: set_h_scroll
methods.description: Set horizontal scroll value.

methods.name: set_v_scroll
methods.description: Set vertical scroll value.

methods.name: get_current_script
methods.description: Returns a [Script] that is currently active in editor.

methods.name: get_open_scripts
methods.description: Returns an array with all [Script] objects which are currently open in editor.

signals.name: editor_script_changed
signals.description: Emitted when user changed active script. Argument is a freshly activated [Script].

signals.name: script_close
signals.description: Emitted when editor is about to close the active script. Argument is a [Script] that is going to be closed.

SegmentShape2D.name: SegmentShape2D
SegmentShape2D.description: Segment Shape for 2D Collision Detection, consists of two points, 'a' and 'b'.

methods.name: get_a
methods.description: Return the first point's position.

methods.name: get_b
methods.description: Return the second point's position.

methods.name: set_a
methods.description: Set the first point's position.

methods.name: set_b
methods.description: Set the second point's position.

Semaphore.name: Semaphore
Semaphore.description: A synchronization Semaphore. Element used in multi-threadding. Initialized to zero on creation.

methods.name: post
methods.description: Lowers the [Semaphore], allowing one more thread in.

methods.name: wait
methods.description: Tries to wait for the [Semaphore], if its value is zero, blocks until non-zero.

Separator.name: Separator
Separator.description: Separator is a [Control] used for separating other controls. It's purely a visual decoration. Horizontal ([HSeparator]) and Vertical ([VSeparator]) versions are available.

Shape2D.name: Shape2D
Shape2D.description: Base class for all 2D Shapes. All 2D shape types inherit from this.

methods.name: collide
methods.description:
Return whether this shape is colliding with another.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), and the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]).

methods.name: collide_and_get_contacts
methods.description:
Return a list of the points where this shape touches another. If there are no collisions, the list is empty.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), and the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]).

methods.name: collide_with_motion
methods.description:
Return whether this shape would collide with another, if a given movement was applied.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the movement to test on this shape ([code]local_motion[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]), and the movement to test onto the other object ([code]shape_motion[/code]).

methods.name: collide_with_motion_and_get_contacts
methods.description:
Return a list of the points where this shape would touch another, if a given movement was applied. If there are no collisions, the list is empty.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the movement to test on this shape ([code]local_motion[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]), and the movement to test onto the other object ([code]shape_motion[/code]).

methods.name: get_custom_solver_bias
methods.description: Return the custom solver bias.

methods.name: set_custom_solver_bias
methods.description:
Use a custom solver bias. No need to change this unless you really know what you are doing.
				The solver bias is a factor controlling how much two objects "rebound" off each other, when colliding, to avoid them getting into each other because of numerical imprecision.

Skeleton.name: Skeleton
Skeleton.brief_description: Skeleton for characters and animated objects.
Skeleton.description: Skeleton provides a hierarchical interface for managing bones, including pose, rest and animation (see [Animation]). Skeleton will support rag doll dynamics in the future.

methods.name: add_bone
methods.description: Add a bone, with name "name". [method get_bone_count] will become the bone index.

methods.name: bind_child_node_to_bone
methods.description: Deprecated soon.

methods.name: clear_bones
methods.description: Clear all the bones in this skeleton.

methods.name: find_bone
methods.description: Return the bone index that matches "name" as its name.

methods.name: get_bone_count
methods.description: Return the amount of bones in the skeleton.

methods.name: get_bone_name
methods.description: Return the name of the bone at index "index"

methods.name: get_bone_parent
methods.description: Return the bone index which is the parent of the bone at "bone_idx". If -1, then bone has no parent. Note that the parent bone returned will always be less than "bone_idx".

methods.name: get_bone_pose
methods.description: Return the pose transform for bone "bone_idx".

methods.name: get_bone_rest
methods.description: Return the rest transform for a bone "bone_idx".

methods.name: get_bound_child_nodes_to_bone
methods.description: Deprecated soon.

methods.name: set_bone_parent
methods.description: Set the bone index "parent_idx" as the parent of the bone at "bone_idx". If -1, then bone has no parent. Note: "parent_idx" must be less than "bone_idx".

methods.name: set_bone_pose
methods.description: Return the pose transform for bone "bone_idx".

methods.name: set_bone_rest
methods.description: Set the rest transform for bone "bone_idx"

methods.name: unbind_child_node_from_bone
methods.description: Deprecated soon.

methods.name: get_ticks
methods.description: Return amounts of ticks to display on slider.

methods.name: get_ticks_on_borders
methods.description: Return true if ticks are visible on borders.

methods.name: set_ticks
methods.description: Set amount of ticks to display in slider.

methods.name: set_ticks_on_borders
methods.description: Set true if ticks are visible on borders.

Spatial.name: Spatial
Spatial.description: Spatial is the base for every type of 3D [Node]. It contains a 3D [Transform] which can be set or get as local or global. If a Spatial [Node] has Spatial children, their transforms will be relative to the parent.

methods.name: get_global_transform
methods.description: Return the global transform, relative to worldspace.

methods.name: get_parent_spatial
methods.description: Return the parent [Spatial], or an empty [Object] if no parent exists or parent is not of type [Spatial].

methods.name: get_rotation
methods.description: Return the rotation (in radians).

methods.name: get_rotation_deg
methods.description: Return the rotation (in degrees).

methods.name: get_transform
methods.description: Return the local transform, relative to the bone parent.

methods.name: set_global_transform
methods.description: Set the transform globally, relative to worldspace.

methods.name: set_rotation
methods.description: Set the rotation (in radians).

methods.name: set_rotation_deg
methods.description: Set the rotation (in degrees).

methods.name: set_transform
methods.description: Set the transform locally, relative to the parent spatial node.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_TRANSFORM_CHANGED
constants.description: Spatial nodes receive this notification with their global transform changes. This means that either the current or a parent node changed its transform.

SpinBox.name: SpinBox
SpinBox.description: SpinBox is a numerical input text field. It allows entering integers and floats.

methods.name: get_suffix
methods.description: Return the specific suffix.

methods.name: is_editable
methods.description: Return if the spinbox is editable.

methods.name: set_editable
methods.description: Set whether the spinbox is editable.

methods.name: set_prefix
methods.description: Set a prefix.

methods.name: set_suffix
methods.description: Set a specific suffix.

SplitContainer.name: SplitContainer
SplitContainer.description: Container for splitting two controls vertically or horizontally, with a grabber that allows adjusting the split offset or ratio.

methods.name: get_dragger_visibility
methods.description: Return visibility of the split dragger (one of [DRAGGER_VISIBLE], [DRAGGER_HIDDEN] or [DRAGGER_HIDDEN_COLLAPSED]).

methods.name: get_split_offset
methods.description: Return the split offset.

methods.name: is_collapsed
methods.description: Return true if the split is collapsed.

methods.name: set_collapsed
methods.description: Set if the split must be collapsed.

methods.name: set_dragger_visibility
methods.description: Set visibility of the split dragger ([i]mode[/i] must be one of [DRAGGER_VISIBLE], [DRAGGER_HIDDEN] or [DRAGGER_HIDDEN_COLLAPSED]).

methods.name: set_split_offset
methods.description: Set the split offset.

signals.name: dragged
signals.description: Emitted when the dragger is dragged by user.

constants.name: DRAGGER_HIDDEN_COLLAPSED
constants.description: The split dragger is invisible and collapsed.

SpotLight.name: SpotLight
SpotLight.brief_description: Spotlight [Light], such as a reflector spotlight or a lantern.
SpotLight.description: A SpotLight light is a type of [Light] node that emits lights in a specific direction, in the shape of a cone. The light is attenuated through the distance and this attenuation can be configured by changing the energy, radius and attenuation parameters of [Light]. TODO: Image of a spotlight.

Sprite.name: Sprite
Sprite.description: General purpose Sprite node. This Sprite node can show any texture as a sprite. The texture can be used as a spritesheet for animation, or only a region from a bigger texture can referenced, like an atlas.

methods.name: get_frame
methods.description: Return the texture frame for a sprite-sheet, works when vframes or hframes are greater than 1.

methods.name: get_hframes
methods.description: Return the amount of horizontal frames. See [method set_hframes].

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return sprite draw offset.

methods.name: get_region_rect
methods.description: Return the region rect to read from.

methods.name: get_texture
methods.description: Return the base texture for the sprite.

methods.name: get_vframes
methods.description: Return the amount of vertical frames. See [method set_vframes].

methods.name: is_centered
methods.description: Return if the sprite is centered at the local origin.

methods.name: is_flipped_h
methods.description: Return true if the sprite is flipped horizontally.

methods.name: is_flipped_v
methods.description: Return true if the sprite is flipped vertically.

methods.name: is_region
methods.description: Return if the sprite reads from a region.

methods.name: set_centered
methods.description: Set whether the sprite should be centered on the origin.

methods.name: set_flip_h
methods.description: Set true to flip the sprite horizontally.

methods.name: set_flip_v
methods.description: Set true to flip the sprite vertically.

methods.name: set_frame
methods.description: Set the texture frame for a sprite-sheet, works when vframes or hframes are greater than 1.

methods.name: set_hframes
methods.description: Set the amount of horizontal frames and converts the sprite into a sprite-sheet. This is useful for animation.

methods.name: set_offset
methods.description: Set the sprite draw offset, useful for setting rotation pivots.

methods.name: set_region
methods.description: Set the sprite as a sub-region of a bigger texture. Useful for texture-atlases.

methods.name: set_region_rect
methods.description: Set the region rect to read from.

methods.name: set_texture
methods.description: Set the base texture for the sprite.

methods.name: set_vframes
methods.description: Set the amount of vertical frames and converts the sprite into a sprite-sheet. This is useful for animation.

StaticBody.name: StaticBody
StaticBody.description:
Static body for 3D Physics. A static body is a simple body that is not intended to move. They don't consume any CPU resources in contrast to a [RigidBody3D] so they are great for scenario collision.
		A static body can also be animated by using simulated motion mode. This is useful for implementing functionalities such as moving platforms. When this mode is active the body can be animated and automatically computes linear and angular velocity to apply in that frame and to influence other bodies.
		Alternatively, a constant linear or angular velocity can be set for the static body, so even if it doesn't move, it affects other bodies as if it was moving (this is useful for simulating conveyor belts or conveyor wheels).

methods.name: get_bounce
methods.description: Return the body bounciness.

methods.name: get_constant_angular_velocity
methods.description: Return the constant angular velocity for the body.

methods.name: get_constant_linear_velocity
methods.description: Return the constant linear velocity for the body.

methods.name: get_friction
methods.description: Return the body friction.

methods.name: set_bounce
methods.description: Set the body bounciness, from 0 (not bouncy) to 1 (bouncy).

methods.name: set_constant_angular_velocity
methods.description: Set a constant angular velocity for the body. This does not rotate the body, but affects other bodies touching it, as if it was rotating.

methods.name: set_constant_linear_velocity
methods.description: Set a constant linear velocity for the body. This does not move the body, but affects other bodies touching it, as if it was moving.

methods.name: set_friction
methods.description: Set the body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (full friction).

StaticBody2D.name: StaticBody2D
StaticBody2D.description:
Static body for 2D Physics. A static body is a simple body that is not intended to move. They don't consume any CPU resources in contrast to a [RigidBody2D] so they are great for scenario collision.
		A static body can also be animated by using simulated motion mode. This is useful for implementing functionalities such as moving platforms. When this mode is active the body can be animated and automatically computes linear and angular velocity to apply in that frame and to influence other bodies.
		Alternatively, a constant linear or angular velocity can be set for the static body, so even if it doesn't move, it affects other bodies as if it was moving (this is useful for simulating conveyor belts or conveyor wheels).

methods.name: get_bounce
methods.description: Return the body bounciness.

methods.name: get_constant_angular_velocity
methods.description: Return the constant angular velocity for the body.

methods.name: get_constant_linear_velocity
methods.description: Return the constant linear velocity for the body.

methods.name: get_friction
methods.description: Return the body friction.

methods.name: set_bounce
methods.description: Set the body bounciness, from 0 (not bouncy) to 1 (bouncy).

methods.name: set_constant_angular_velocity
methods.description: Set a constant angular velocity for the body. This does not rotate the body, but affects other bodies touching it, as if it was rotating.

methods.name: set_constant_linear_velocity
methods.description: Set a constant linear velocity for the body. This does not move the body, but affects other bodies touching it, as if it was moving.

methods.name: set_friction
methods.description: Set the body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (full friction).

StreamPeer.name: StreamPeer
StreamPeer.brief_description: Abstraction and base class for stream-based protocols.
StreamPeer.description: StreamPeer is an abstraction and base class for stream-based protocols (such as TCP or Unix Sockets). It provides an API for sending and receiving data through streams as raw data or strings.

methods.name: get_16
methods.description: Get a signed 16 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_32
methods.description: Get a signed 32 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_64
methods.description: Get a signed 64 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_8
methods.description: Get a signed byte from the stream.

methods.name: get_available_bytes
methods.description: Return the amount of bytes this [StreamPeer] has available.

methods.name: get_data
methods.description: Return a chunk data with the received bytes. The amount of bytes to be received can be requested in the "bytes" argument. If not enough bytes are available, the function will block until the desired amount is received. This function returns two values, an Error code and a data array.

methods.name: get_double
methods.description: Get a double-precision float from the stream.

methods.name: get_float
methods.description: Get a single-precision float from the stream.

methods.name: get_partial_data
methods.description: Return a chunk data with the received bytes. The amount of bytes to be received can be requested in the "bytes" argument. If not enough bytes are available, the function will return how many were actually received. This function returns two values, an Error code, and a data array.

methods.name: get_string
methods.description: Get a string with byte-length "bytes" from the stream.

methods.name: get_u16
methods.description: Get an unsigned 16 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_u32
methods.description: Get an unsigned 32 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_u64
methods.description: Get an unsigned 16 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_u8
methods.description: Get an unsigned byte from the stream.

methods.name: get_utf8_string
methods.description: Get an utf8 string with byte-length "bytes" from the stream (this decodes the string sent as utf8).

methods.name: get_var
methods.description: Get a Variant from the stream.

methods.name: is_big_endian_enabled
methods.description: Return whether this [StreamPeer] is using big-endian format.

methods.name: put_16
methods.description: Put a signed 16 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_32
methods.description: Put a signed 32 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_64
methods.description: Put a signed 64 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_8
methods.description: Put a signed byte into the stream.

methods.name: put_data
methods.description: Send a chunk of data through the connection, blocking if necessary until the data is done sending. This function returns an Error code.

methods.name: put_double
methods.description: Put a double-precision float into the stream.

methods.name: put_float
methods.description: Put a single-precision float into the stream.

methods.name: put_partial_data
methods.description: Send a chunk of data through the connection, if all the data could not be sent at once, only part of it will. This function returns two values, an Error code and an integer, describing how much data was actually sent.

methods.name: put_u16
methods.description: Put an unsigned 16 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_u32
methods.description: Put an unsigned 32 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_u64
methods.description: Put an unsigned 64 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_u8
methods.description: Put an unsigned byte into the stream.

methods.name: put_utf8_string
methods.description: Put a zero-terminated utf8 string into the stream.

methods.name: put_var
methods.description: Put a Variant into the stream.

methods.name: set_big_endian
methods.description: Set this [StreamPeer] to use big-endian format. Default is false.

StreamPeerSSL.name: StreamPeerSSL
StreamPeerSSL.description: SSL Stream peer. This object can be used to connect to SSL servers.

methods.name: connect_to_stream
methods.description: Connect to a peer using an underlying [StreamPeer] "stream", when "validate_certs" is true, [StreamPeerSSL] will validate that the certificate presented by the peer matches the "for_hostname".

methods.name: disconnect_from_stream
methods.description: Disconnect from host.

methods.name: get_status
methods.description: Return the status of the connection, one of STATUS_* enum.

constants.name: STATUS_DISCONNECTED
constants.description: A status representing a [StreamPeerSSL] that is disconnected.

constants.name: STATUS_CONNECTED
constants.description: A status representing a [StreamPeerSSL] that is connected to a host.

constants.name: STATUS_ERROR_NO_CERTIFICATE
constants.description: An errot status that shows the peer did not present a SSL certificate and validation was requested.

constants.name: STATUS_ERROR_HOSTNAME_MISMATCH
constants.description: An error status that shows a mismatch in the SSL certificate domain presented by the host and the domain requested for validation.

StreamPeerTCP.name: StreamPeerTCP
StreamPeerTCP.description: TCP Stream peer. This object can be used to connect to TCP servers, or also is returned by a tcp server.

methods.name: connect_to_host
methods.description: Connect to the specified host:port pair. A hostname will be resolved if valid. Returns [OK] on success or [FAILED] on failure.

methods.name: disconnect_from_host
methods.description: Disconnect from host.

methods.name: get_connected_host
methods.description: Return the IP of this peer.

methods.name: get_connected_port
methods.description: Return the port of this peer.

methods.name: get_status
methods.description: Return the status of the connection, one of STATUS_* enum.

constants.name: STATUS_NONE
constants.description: The initial status of the [StreamPeerTCP], also the status after a disconnect.

constants.name: STATUS_CONNECTING
constants.description: A status representing a [StreamPeerTCP] that is connecting to a host.

constants.name: STATUS_CONNECTED
constants.description: A status representing a [StreamPeerTCP] that is connected to a host.

constants.name: STATUS_ERROR
constants.description: A staus representing a [StreamPeerTCP] in error state.

String.name: String
String.description: This is the built-in string class (and the one used by GDScript). It supports Unicode and provides all necessary means for string handling. Strings are reference counted and use a copy-on-write approach, so passing them around is cheap in resources.

methods.name: begins_with
methods.description: Return true if the strings begins with the given string.

methods.name: bigrams
methods.description: Return the bigrams (pairs of consecutive letters) of this string.

methods.name: c_escape
methods.description: Return a copy of the string with special characters escaped using the C language standard.

methods.name: c_unescape
methods.description: Return a copy of the string with escaped characters replaced by their meanings according to the C language standard.

methods.name: capitalize
methods.description: Change the case of some letters. Replace underscores with spaces, convert all letters to lowercase then capitalize first and every letter following the space character. For [code]capitalize camelCase mixed_with_underscores[/code] it will return [code]Capitalize Camelcase Mixed With Underscores[/code].

methods.name: casecmp_to
methods.description: Perform a case-sensitive comparison to another string, return -1 if less, 0 if equal and +1 if greater.

methods.name: empty
methods.description: Return true if the string is empty.

methods.name: ends_with
methods.description: Return true if the strings ends with the given string.

methods.name: erase
methods.description: Erase [code]chars[/code] characters from the string starting from [code]pos[/code].

methods.name: find
methods.description: Find the first occurrence of a substring, return the starting position of the substring or -1 if not found. Optionally, the initial search index can be passed.

methods.name: find_last
methods.description: Find the last occurrence of a substring, return the starting position of the substring or -1 if not found. Optionally, the initial search index can be passed.

methods.name: findn
methods.description: Find the first occurrence of a substring but search as case-insensitive, return the starting position of the substring or -1 if not found. Optionally, the initial search index can be passed.

methods.name: get_base_dir
methods.description: If the string is a path to a file, return the base directory.

methods.name: get_basename

methods.name: get_extension

methods.name: get_file
methods.description: If the string is a path to a file, return the file and ignore the base directory.

methods.name: hash

methods.name: hex_to_int
methods.description: Convert a string containing an hexadecimal number into an int.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a substring at a given position.

methods.name: is_abs_path
methods.description: If the string is a path to a file or directory, return true if the path is absolute.

methods.name: is_rel_path
methods.description: If the string is a path to a file or directory, return true if the path is relative.

methods.name: is_subsequence_of
methods.description: Check whether this string is a subsequence of the given string.

methods.name: is_subsequence_ofi
methods.description: Check whether this string is a subsequence of the given string, without considering case.

methods.name: is_valid_float
methods.description: Check whether the string contains a valid float.

methods.name: is_valid_html_color
methods.description: Check whether the string contains a valid color in HTML notation.

methods.name: is_valid_identifier
methods.description: Check whether the string is a valid identifier. As is common in programming languages, a valid identifier may contain only letters, digits and underscores (_) and the first character may not be a digit.

methods.name: is_valid_integer
methods.description: Check whether the string contains a valid integer.

methods.name: is_valid_ip_address
methods.description: Check whether the string contains a valid IP address.

methods.name: json_escape
methods.description: Return a copy of the string with special characters escaped using the JSON standard.

methods.name: left
methods.description: Return an amount of characters from the left of the string.

methods.name: length
methods.description: Return the length of the string in characters.

methods.name: match
methods.description: Do a simple expression match, where '*' matches zero or more arbitrary characters and '?' matches any single character except '.'.

methods.name: matchn
methods.description: Do a simple case insensitive expression match, using ? and * wildcards (see [method match]).

methods.name: md5_buffer
methods.description: Return the MD5 hash of the string as an array of bytes.

methods.name: md5_text
methods.description: Return the MD5 hash of the string as a string.

methods.name: nocasecmp_to
methods.description: Perform a case-insensitive comparison to another string, return -1 if less, 0 if equal and +1 if greater.

methods.name: ord_at
methods.description: Return the character code at position [code]at[/code].

methods.name: pad_decimals
methods.description: Format a number to have an exact number of [code]digits[/code] after the decimal point.

methods.name: pad_zeros
methods.description: Format a number to have an exact number of [code]digits[/code] before the decimal point.

methods.name: percent_decode
methods.description: Decode a percent-encoded string. See [method percent_encode].

methods.name: percent_encode
methods.description: Percent-encode a string. This is meant to encode parameters in a URL when sending a HTTP GET request and bodies of form-urlencoded POST request.

methods.name: plus_file
methods.description: If the string is a path, this concatenates [code]file[/code] at the end of the string as a subpath. E.g. [code]"this/is".plus_file("path") == "this/is/path"[/code].

methods.name: replace
methods.description: Replace occurrences of a substring for different ones inside the string.

methods.name: replacen
methods.description: Replace occurrences of a substring for different ones inside the string, but search case-insensitive.

methods.name: rfind
methods.description: Perform a search for a substring, but start from the end of the string instead of the beginning.

methods.name: rfindn
methods.description: Perform a search for a substring, but start from the end of the string instead of the beginning. Also search case-insensitive.

methods.name: right
methods.description: Return the right side of the string from a given position.

methods.name: sha256_text
methods.description: Return the SHA-256 hash of the string as a string.

methods.name: similarity
methods.description: Return the similarity index of the text compared to this string. 1 means totally similar and 0 means totally dissimilar.

methods.name: split
methods.description: Split the string by a divisor string, return an array of the substrings. Example "One,Two,Three" will return ["One","Two","Three"] if split by ",".

methods.name: split_floats
methods.description: Split the string in floats by using a divisor string, return an array of the substrings. Example "1,2.5,3" will return [1,2.5,3] if split by ",".

methods.name: strip_edges
methods.description: Return a copy of the string stripped of any non-printable character at the beginning and the end. The optional arguments are used to toggle stripping on the left and right edges respectively.

methods.name: substr
methods.description: Return part of the string from the position [code]from[/code], with length [code]len[/code].

methods.name: to_ascii
methods.description: Convert the String (which is a character array) to PoolByteArray (which is an array of bytes). The conversion is speeded up in comparison to to_utf8() with the assumption that all the characters the String contains are only ASCII characters.

methods.name: to_float
methods.description: Convert a string, containing a decimal number, into a [code]float[/code].

methods.name: to_int
methods.description: Convert a string, containing an integer number, into an [code]int[/code].

methods.name: to_lower
methods.description: Return the string converted to lowercase.

methods.name: to_upper
methods.description: Return the string converted to uppercase.

methods.name: to_utf8
methods.description: Convert the String (which is an array of characters) to PoolByteArray (which is an array of bytes). The conversion is a bit slower than to_ascii(), but supports all UTF-8 characters. Therefore, you should prefer this function over to_ascii().

methods.name: xml_escape
methods.description: Return a copy of the string with special characters escaped using the XML standard.

methods.name: xml_unescape
methods.description: Return a copy of the string with escaped characters replaced by their meanings according to the XML standard.

StyleBox.name: StyleBox
StyleBox.brief_description: Base class for drawing stylized boxes for the UI.
StyleBox.description: StyleBox is [Resource] that provides an abstract base class for drawing stylized boxes for the UI. StyleBoxes are used for drawing the styles of buttons, line edit backgrounds, tree backgrounds, etc. and also for testing a transparency mask for pointer signals. If mask test fails on a StyleBox assigned as mask to a control, clicks and motion signals will go through it to the one below.

methods.name: get_default_margin
methods.description: Return the default offset of the margin "margin" (see MARGIN_* enum) of a StyleBox, Controls that draw styleboxes with context inside need to know the margin, so the border of the stylebox is not occluded.

methods.name: get_margin
methods.description: Return the offset of margin "margin" (see MARGIN_* enum).

methods.name: get_minimum_size
methods.description: Return the minimum size that this stylebox can be shrunk to.

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return the "offset" of a stylebox, this is a helper function, like writing [code]Vector2(style.get_margin(MARGIN_LEFT), style.get_margin(MARGIN_TOP))[/code].

methods.name: set_default_margin
methods.description: Set the default offset "offset" of the margin "margin" (see MARGIN_* enum) for a StyleBox, Controls that draw styleboxes with context inside need to know the margin, so the border of the stylebox is not occluded.

methods.name: test_mask
methods.description: Test a position in a rectangle, return whether it passes the mask test.

StyleBoxEmpty.name: StyleBoxEmpty
StyleBoxEmpty.description: Empty stylebox (really does not display anything).

StyleBoxFlat.name: StyleBoxFlat
StyleBoxFlat.description: Stylebox of a single color. Displays the stylebox of a single color, alternatively a border with light/dark colors can be assigned.

StyleBoxTexture.name: StyleBoxTexture
StyleBoxTexture.description: Texture Based 3x3 scale style. This stylebox performs a 3x3 scaling of a texture, where only the center cell is fully stretched. This allows for the easy creation of bordered styles.

SurfaceTool.name: SurfaceTool
SurfaceTool.description:
The [SurfaceTool] is used to construct a [Mesh] by specifying vertex attributes individually. It can be used to construct a [Mesh] from script. All properties except index need to be added before a call to [method add_vertex]. For example adding vertex colors and UVs looks like
		[codeblock]
		var st = SurfaceTool.new()
		st.begin(Mesh.PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES)
		st.add_color(Color(1, 0, 0))
		st.add_uv(Vector2(0, 0))
		st.add_vertex(Vector3(0, 0, 0))
		[/codeblock]
		The [SurfaceTool] now contains one vertex of a triangle which has a UV coordinate and a specified [Color]. If another vertex were added without calls to [method add_uv] or [method add_color] then the last values would be used.
		It is very important that vertex attributes are passed [b]before[/b] the call to [method add_vertex], failure to do this will result in an error when committing the vertex information to a mesh.

methods.name: add_bones
methods.description: Add an array of bones for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_color
methods.description: Specify a [Color] for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_index
methods.description: Adds an index to index array if you are using indexed Vertices. Does not need to be called before adding Vertex.

methods.name: add_normal
methods.description: Specify a normal for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_smooth_group
methods.description: Specify whether current Vertex (if using only Vertex arrays) or current index (if also using index arrays) should utilize smooth normals for normal calculation.

methods.name: add_tangent
methods.description: Specify a Tangent for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_triangle_fan
methods.description: Insert a triangle fan made of array data into [Mesh] being constructed.

methods.name: add_uv
methods.description: Specify UV Coordinate for next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_uv2
methods.description: Specify an optional second set of UV coordinates for next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_vertex
methods.description: Specify position of current Vertex. Should be called after specifying other vertex properties (e.g. Color, UV).

methods.name: add_weights
methods.description: Specify weight value for next Vertex to use.

methods.name: begin
methods.description: Called before adding any Vertices. Takes the primitive type as an argument (e.g. Mesh.PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES).

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all information passed into the surface tool so far.

methods.name: commit
methods.description: Returns a constructed [Mesh] from current information passed in. If an existing [Mesh] is passed in as an argument, will add an extra surface to the existing [Mesh].

methods.name: deindex
methods.description: Removes index array by expanding Vertex array.

methods.name: generate_normals
methods.description: Generates normals from Vertices so you do not have to do it manually.

methods.name: index
methods.description: Shrinks Vertex array by creating an index array. Avoids reusing Vertices.

methods.name: set_material
methods.description: Sets [Material] to be used by the [Mesh] you are constructing.

TCP_Server.name: TCP_Server
TCP_Server.description: TCP Server class. Listens to connections on a port and returns a [StreamPeerTCP] when got a connection.

methods.name: is_connection_available
methods.description: Return true if a connection is available for taking.

methods.name: listen
methods.description:
Listen on the "port" binding to "bind_address".
				If "bind_address" is set as "*" (default), the server will listen on all available addresses (both IPv4 and IPv6).
				If "bind_address" is set as "0.0.0.0" (for IPv4) or "::" (for IPv6), the server will listen on all available addresses matching that IP type.
				If "bind_address" is set to any valid address (e.g. "192.168.1.101", "::1", etc), the server will only listen on the interface with that addresses (or fail if no interface with the given address exists).

methods.name: stop
methods.description: Stop listening.

methods.name: take_connection
methods.description: If a connection is available, return a StreamPeerTCP with the connection/

TabContainer.name: TabContainer
TabContainer.description:
Tabbed Container. Contains several children controls, but shows only one at the same time. Clicking on the top tabs allows to change the currently visible one.
		Children controls of this one automatically.

methods.name: are_tabs_visible
methods.description: Return whether the tabs should be visible or hidden.

methods.name: get_current_tab
methods.description: Return the current tab index that is being shown.

methods.name: get_previous_tab
methods.description: Return the previous tab index that was being shown.

methods.name: get_tab_align
methods.description: Return tab alignment, from the ALIGN_* enum.

methods.name: get_tab_control
methods.description: Return the current tab control that is being shown.

methods.name: get_tab_count
methods.description: Return the amount of tabs.

methods.name: get_tab_title
methods.description: Return the title for the tab. Tab titles are by default the children node name, but this can be overridden.

methods.name: set_current_tab
methods.description: Bring a tab (and the Control it represents) to the front, and hide the rest.

methods.name: set_tab_align
methods.description: Set tab alignment, from the ALIGN_* enum. Moves tabs to the left, right or center.

methods.name: set_tab_icon
methods.description: Set an icon for a tab.

methods.name: set_tab_title
methods.description: Set a title for the tab. Tab titles are by default the children node name, but this can be overridden.

methods.name: set_tabs_visible
methods.description: Set whether the tabs should be visible or hidden.

signals.name: tab_changed
signals.description: Emitted only when the current tab changes.

signals.name: tab_selected
signals.description: Emitted when a tab is being selected, even if it is the same tab.

Tabs.name: Tabs
Tabs.description: Simple tabs control, similar to [TabContainer] but is only in charge of drawing tabs, not interact with children.

methods.name: get_tab_rect
methods.description: Returns tab [Rect2] with local position and size.

methods.name: move_tab
methods.description: Rearrange tab.

TextEdit.name: TextEdit
TextEdit.description: TextEdit is meant for editing large, multiline text. It also has facilities for editing code, such as syntax highlighting support and multiple levels of undo/redo.

methods.name: add_color_region
methods.description: Add color region (given the delimiters) and its colors.

methods.name: add_keyword_color
methods.description: Add a keyword and its color.

methods.name: clear_colors
methods.description: Clear all the syntax coloring information.

methods.name: clear_undo_history
methods.description: Clear the undo history.

methods.name: copy
methods.description: Copy the current selection.

methods.name: cursor_get_blink_enabled

methods.name: cursor_get_blink_speed
methods.description: Gets the text editor caret blink speed.

methods.name: cursor_get_column

methods.name: cursor_get_line
methods.description: Return the line the editing cursor is at.

methods.name: cursor_is_block_mode
methods.description: Gets whether the text editor caret is in block mode.

methods.name: cursor_set_blink_enabled
methods.description: Set the text editor caret to blink.

methods.name: cursor_set_blink_speed
methods.description: Set the text editor caret blink speed. Cannot be less then or equal to 0.

methods.name: cursor_set_block_mode
methods.description: Set the text editor caret to block mode.

methods.name: cut
methods.description: Cut the current selection.

methods.name: get_line
methods.description: Return the text of a specific line.

methods.name: get_line_count
methods.description: Return the amount of total lines in the text.

methods.name: get_selection_from_column
methods.description: Return the selection begin column.

methods.name: get_selection_from_line
methods.description: Return the selection begin line.

methods.name: get_selection_text
methods.description: Return the text inside the selection.

methods.name: get_selection_to_column
methods.description: Return the selection end column.

methods.name: get_selection_to_line
methods.description: Return the selection end line.

methods.name: get_text
methods.description: Return the whole text.

methods.name: insert_text_at_cursor
methods.description: Insert a given text at the cursor position.

methods.name: is_highlight_all_occurrences_enabled
methods.description: Returns true if highlight all occurrences is enabled.

methods.name: is_selection_active
methods.description: Return true if the selection is active.

methods.name: is_show_line_numbers_enabled
methods.description: Returns true if line numbers are enabled.

methods.name: is_syntax_coloring_enabled
methods.description: Return true if the syntax coloring is enabled.

methods.name: paste
methods.description: Paste the current selection.

methods.name: redo
methods.description: Perform redo operation.

methods.name: search
methods.description: Perform a search inside the text. Search flags can be specified in the SEARCH_* enum.

methods.name: select
methods.description: Perform selection, from line/column to line/column.

methods.name: select_all
methods.description: Select all the text.

methods.name: set_highlight_all_occurrences
methods.description: Set to enable highlighting all occurrences of the current selection.

methods.name: set_max_chars
methods.description: Set the maximum amount of characters editable.

methods.name: set_readonly
methods.description: Set the text editor as read-only. Text can be displayed but not edited.

methods.name: set_show_line_numbers
methods.description: Set to enable showing line numbers.

methods.name: set_syntax_coloring
methods.description: Set to enable the syntax coloring.

methods.name: set_text
methods.description: Set the entire text.

methods.name: set_wrap
methods.description: Enable text wrapping when it goes beyond he edge of what is visible.

methods.name: undo
methods.description: Perform undo operation.

signals.name: breakpoint_toggled
signals.description: Emitted when a breakpoint is placed via the breakpoint gutter.

signals.name: cursor_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the cursor changes.

signals.name: text_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the text changes.

Texture.name: Texture
Texture.description: A texture works by registering an image in the video hardware, which then can be used in 3D models or 2D [Sprite] or GUI [Control].

methods.name: get_flags
methods.description: Return the current texture flags.

methods.name: get_height
methods.description: Return the texture height.

methods.name: get_size
methods.description: Return the texture size.

methods.name: get_width
methods.description: Return the texture width.

methods.name: set_flags
methods.description: Change the texture flags.

constants.name: FLAG_MIPMAPS
constants.description: Generate mipmaps, to enable smooth zooming out of the texture.

constants.name: FLAG_FILTER
constants.description: Turn on magnifying filter, to enable smooth zooming in of the texture.

constants.name: FLAGS_DEFAULT
constants.description: Default flags. Generate mipmaps, repeat, and filter are enabled.

TextureButton.name: TextureButton
TextureButton.brief_description: Button that can be themed with textures.
TextureButton.description:
Button that can be themed with textures. This is like a regular [Button] but can be themed by assigning textures to it. This button is intended to be easy to theme, however a regular button can expand (that uses styleboxes) and still be better if the interface is expect to have internationalization of texts.
		Only the normal texture is required, the others are optional.

TextureProgress.name: TextureProgress
TextureProgress.description: [ProgressBar] implementation that is easier to theme (by just passing a few textures).

TextureRect.name: TextureRect
TextureRect.brief_description: Control Frame that draws a texture.
TextureRect.description: Control frame that simply draws an assigned texture. It can stretch or not. It's a simple way to just show an image in a UI.

Theme.name: Theme
Theme.description:
Theme for skinning controls. Controls can be skinned individually, but for complex applications it's more efficient to just create a global theme that defines everything. This theme can be applied to any [Control], and it and its children will automatically use it.
		Theme resources can be alternatively loaded by writing them in a .theme file, see docs for more info.

Thread.name: Thread
Thread.brief_description: A unit of execution in a process.
Thread.description: A unit of execution in a process. Can run methods on [Object]\ s simultaneously. The use of synchronization via [Mutex], [Semaphore] is advised if working with shared objects.

methods.name: get_id
methods.description: Return the id of the thread, uniquely identifying it among all threads.

methods.name: is_active
methods.description: Whether this thread is currently active, an active Thread cannot start work on a new method but can be joined with [method wait_to_finish].

methods.name: start
methods.description:
Start a new [Thread], it will run "method" on object "instance" using "userdata" as an argument and running with "priority", one of PRIORITY_* enum.
				Returns OK on success, or ERR_CANT_CREATE on failure.

methods.name: wait_to_finish
methods.description: Joins the [Thread] and waits for it to finish. Returns what the method called returned.

TileMap.name: TileMap
TileMap.description:
Node for 2D tile-based games. Tilemaps use a [TileSet] which contain a list of tiles (textures, their rect and a collision) and are used to create complex grid-based maps.
		To optimize drawing and culling (sort of like [GridMap]), you can specify a quadrant size, so chunks of the map will be batched together at drawing time.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all cells.

methods.name: get_cell
methods.description: Return the tile index of the referenced cell.

methods.name: get_cell_size
methods.description: Return the cell size.

methods.name: get_cellv
methods.description: Return the tile index of the cell referenced by a Vector2.

methods.name: get_center_x
methods.description: Return true if tiles are to be centered in x coordinate (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: get_center_y
methods.description: Return true if tiles are to be centered in y coordinate (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: get_collision_bounce
methods.description: Return the collision bounce parameter.

methods.name: get_collision_friction
methods.description: Return the collision friction parameter.

methods.name: get_collision_layer
methods.description: Return the collision layer.

methods.name: get_collision_mask
methods.description: Return the collision mask.

methods.name: get_collision_use_kinematic
methods.description: Return whether the tilemap handles collisions as a kinematic body.

methods.name: get_custom_transform
methods.description: Return the custom transform matrix.

methods.name: get_half_offset
methods.description: Return the current half offset configuration.

methods.name: get_mode
methods.description: Return the orientation mode.

methods.name: get_quadrant_size
methods.description: Return the quadrant size.

methods.name: get_tile_origin
methods.description: Return the tile origin configuration.

methods.name: get_tileset
methods.description: Return the current tileset.

methods.name: get_used_cells
methods.description: Return an array of all cells containing a tile from the tileset (i.e. a tile index different from -1).

methods.name: is_cell_transposed
methods.description: Return whether the referenced cell is transposed, i.e. the X and Y axes are swapped (mirroring with regard to the (1,1) vector).

methods.name: is_cell_x_flipped
methods.description: Return whether the referenced cell is flipped over the X axis.

methods.name: is_cell_y_flipped
methods.description: Return whether the referenced cell is flipped over the Y axis.

methods.name: is_y_sort_mode_enabled
methods.description: Return the Y sort mode.

methods.name: map_to_world
methods.description:
Return the absolute world position corresponding to the tilemap (grid-based) coordinates given as an argument.
				Optionally, the tilemap's potential half offset can be ignored.

methods.name: set_cell
methods.description:
Set the tile index for the cell referenced by its grid-based X and Y coordinates.
				A tile index of -1 clears the cell.
				Optionally, the tile can also be flipped over the X and Y coordinates or transposed.

methods.name: set_cell_size
methods.description: Set the cell size.

methods.name: set_cellv
methods.description:
Set the tile index for the cell referenced by a Vector2 of grid-based coordinates.
				A tile index of -1 clears the cell.
				Optionally, the tile can also be flipped over the X and Y axes or transposed.

methods.name: set_center_x
methods.description: Set tiles to be centered in x coordinate. (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: set_center_y
methods.description: Set tiles to be centered in y coordinate. (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: set_collision_bounce
methods.description: Set the collision bounce parameter. Allowable values range from 0 to 1.

methods.name: set_collision_friction
methods.description: Set the collision friction parameter. Allowable values range from 0 to 1.

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description:
Set the collision layer.
				Layers are referenced by binary indexes, so allowable values to describe the 20 available layers range from 0 to 2^20-1.

methods.name: set_collision_mask
methods.description:
Set the collision masks.
				Masks are referenced by binary indexes, so allowable values to describe the 20 available masks range from 0 to 2^20-1.

methods.name: set_collision_use_kinematic
methods.description: Set the tilemap to handle collisions as a kinematic body (enabled) or a static body (disabled).

methods.name: set_custom_transform
methods.description: Set custom transform matrix, to use in combination with the custom orientation mode.

methods.name: set_half_offset
methods.description:
Set an half offset on the X coordinate, Y coordinate, or none (use HALF_OFFSET_* constants as argument).
				Half offset sets every other tile off by a half tile size in the specified direction.

methods.name: set_mode
methods.description: Set the orientation mode as square, isometric or custom (use MODE_* constants as argument).

methods.name: set_quadrant_size
methods.description:
Set the quadrant size, this optimizes drawing by batching chunks of map at draw/cull time.
				Allowed values are integers ranging from 1 to 128.

methods.name: set_tile_origin
methods.description: Set the tile origin to the tile center or its top-left corner (use TILE_ORIGIN_* constants as argument).

methods.name: set_tileset
methods.description: Set the current tileset.

methods.name: set_y_sort_mode
methods.description:
Set the Y sort mode. Enabled Y sort mode means that children of the tilemap will be drawn in the order defined by their Y coordinate.
				A tile with a higher Y coordinate will therefore be drawn later, potentially covering up the tile(s) above it if its sprite is higher than its cell size.

methods.name: world_to_map
methods.description: Return the tilemap (grid-based) coordinates corresponding to the absolute world position given as an argument.

signals.name: settings_changed
signals.description: Signal indicating that a tilemap setting has changed.

constants.name: INVALID_CELL
constants.description: Returned when a cell doesn't exist.

constants.name: HALF_OFFSET_X
constants.description: Half offset on the X coordinate.

constants.name: HALF_OFFSET_Y
constants.description: Half offset on the Y coordinate.

constants.name: TILE_ORIGIN_TOP_LEFT
constants.description: Tile origin at its top-left corner.

TileSet.name: TileSet
TileSet.description:
A TileSet is a library of tiles for a [TileMap]. It contains a list of tiles, each consisting of a sprite and optional collision shapes.
		Tiles are referenced by a unique integer ID.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all tiles.

methods.name: create_tile
methods.description: Create a new tile which will be referenced by the given ID.

methods.name: find_tile_by_name
methods.description: Find the first tile matching the given name.

methods.name: get_last_unused_tile_id
methods.description: Return the ID following the last currently used ID, useful when creating a new tile.

methods.name: get_tiles_ids
methods.description: Return an array of all currently used tile IDs.

methods.name: remove_tile
methods.description: Remove the tile referenced by the given ID.

methods.name: tile_get_light_occluder
methods.description: Return the light occluder of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_material
methods.description: Return the material of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_name
methods.description: Return the name of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_navigation_polygon
methods.description: Return the navigation polygon of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_navigation_polygon_offset

methods.name: get_rotation
